Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.02,0:00:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Greetings! \NWe’re so happy you could join us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.16,0:00:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a new service year \Nand a new monthly program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.16,0:00:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And look, we have a new cohost, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.16,0:00:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Seth Hyatt, \Naffectionately known as Rocky. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.23,0:00:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Rocky, what can the friends \Nhave to look forward to?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.23,0:00:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look forward \Nto this dramatization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.17,0:00:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where we meet a sister who is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.17,0:00:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,on the brink of losing \Nher joy in the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.24,0:00:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What does she need to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.24,0:00:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We will all benefit \Nfrom the very practical application.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.38,0:00:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re also going to see \Nan amazing video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.05,0:00:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Art Department \Nat world headquarters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.32,0:00:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they do? \NAnd how do we benefit from their work? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.39,0:00:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This segment is going \Nto answer those questions.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.26,0:00:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In some countries in Europe, \Ncongregations are involved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.63,0:00:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in witnessing at truck stops. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.70,0:00:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This has proved to be a very productive way\Nof reaching individuals \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.90,0:00:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who spend most of their time \Naway from home.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.04,0:00:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you’re a first-time viewer, welcome. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.24,0:01:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re a regular viewer, welcome back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.98,0:01:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the September program \Nof JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.43,0:01:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you enjoyed studying the book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.94,0:01:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Imitate Their Faith as much as I have? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.77,0:01:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a wonderful book, \Nisn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.07,0:01:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was particularly captivated \Nby the introduction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.01,0:01:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a point in the introduction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.45,0:01:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that encouraged us \Nto use our imagination \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.15,0:01:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re reading the Bible: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.19,0:01:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the sights, \Nto hear the sounds, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.82,0:01:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to smell the aromas, \Nto try to capture the feelings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.79,0:01:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the individuals \Nthat we are reading about. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.10,0:01:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, we don’t want \Nour imagination to run away with us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.47,0:01:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the same time, \Nwe do want to get \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.77,0:02:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a solid mental picture \Nof what we’re reading. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.34,0:02:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what I’d like \Nto talk to you about today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.14,0:02:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re reading the Bible, \Ntry to get the whole picture.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.01,0:02:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we’ll use a couple \Nof well-known Bible accounts to illustrate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.25,0:02:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been raised \Nin a stepfamily or a blended family? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.22,0:02:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have, \Ndid you know that you have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.33,0:02:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,something in common with Joseph, \Nthe son of Jacob? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.80,0:02:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph was raised \Nwith ten half brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.90,0:02:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in a large blended family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.44,0:02:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you want to try to view \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this family as a composite. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to try to figure out \Nhow did people mesh \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.21,0:02:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or how did they clash \Nwithin this family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.25,0:02:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.25,0:02:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you might start by writing down \Nsome of the characteristics \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.65,0:02:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of the individual members \Nof the family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.09,0:02:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Joseph’s half brothers \Nand Joseph himself? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.23,0:02:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you know about them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.23,0:03:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Judah, \NSimeon, Levi, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.10,0:03:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dan, Naphtali\N—what do you know? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.90,0:03:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So write down \Ntheir characteristics, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to figure out \Nhow they might get along. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes there is \None individual incident \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.85,0:03:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s recorded in the Bible,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.85,0:03:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but we mustn’t forget:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.08,0:03:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,People’s actions \Nhave a way of affecting other people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.32,0:03:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you read \Nabout a certain incident in the Bible,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.39,0:03:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,try to imagine who \Nmight have been affected by that incident.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.86,0:03:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Take an example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.56,0:03:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book of Genesis, \Nwe read that Jacob’s son Reuben \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.37,0:03:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,committed sexual immorality \Nwith Bilhah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.57,0:03:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that had an effect \Non other people without doubt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.74,0:03:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was Reuben? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.75,0:03:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He was Leah’s oldest son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was Bilhah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.48,0:03:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Rachel’s handmaiden. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.49,0:03:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that there might have been \Na little animosity or tension \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.02,0:04:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,between Leah and Rachel sometimes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.69,0:04:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,especially when you consider \Nhow their marriages started out? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.40,0:04:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There may have been. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And it may be \Nthat the attitudes of the women \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.17,0:04:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,had some bearing on the attitudes\Nof their sons as well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.94,0:04:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So you take all of these things \Ninto consideration. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.01,0:04:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Bilhah had two sons, \NDan and Naphtali. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.41,0:04:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you think \Nthey felt when they learned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.72,0:04:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that their oldest brother, \Nor half brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.82,0:04:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,had committed fornication \Nwith their mother? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.79,0:04:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So there could have been \Ntension there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.06,0:04:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And this all goes into the mix \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.26,0:04:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re considering \Nthe family as a composite.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.43,0:04:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, do you picture \NJoseph at age 17 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.77,0:04:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,with ten much older half brothers, \Nmaybe in their 30’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.71,0:04:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,some old enough to be his father? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.58,0:04:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Not true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.58,0:04:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is that there was only \Na seven-year age difference \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.72,0:05:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,between Joseph’s oldest brother, \NReuben, and Joseph himself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.52,0:05:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, 11 of Jacob’s sons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.22,0:05:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,were born \Nduring the seven-year period \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.99,0:05:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jacob \Nwas working for Laban. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.30,0:05:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Eleven sons in seven years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.47,0:05:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,how is that possible? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.47,0:05:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s easy, when you remember \Nthat Jacob had two wives\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.14,0:05:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and two concubines, \Nor secondary wives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.07,0:05:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So there didn’t have to be \Na nine-month interval \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.98,0:05:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,between the birth \Nof the children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.35,0:05:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, some could have been born \Njust about at the same time; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.88,0:05:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,they could have been \Nthe same age. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.45,0:05:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Joseph \Nwas sold into slavery at age 17, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.92,0:05:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,his oldest brother \Nwas no more than 24. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.79,0:05:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of his brothers were only \Na year or two older than Joseph himself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.67,0:05:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re talking \Nabout a group of young men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.30,0:05:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in their late teens \Nand early 20’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.94,0:05:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and this might explain \Nsome of the hotheaded reactions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.67,0:06:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that some \Nof those young men had.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.15,0:06:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, so much for the boys. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.15,0:06:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What about their father, Jacob? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.25,0:06:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we learn about him? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, \Nhe was a spiritual man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.06,0:06:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is something \Nfor you young brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.86,0:06:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,who are contemplating \Nmarriage to think about. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.66,0:06:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob was willing \Nto go to any length \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep his relationship \Nwith Jehovah intact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.13,0:06:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take an example: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.14,0:06:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis 29:18. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.14,0:06:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can follow along \Non the screen as I read this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re talking \Nabout marriage here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.28,0:06:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis 29:18.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.38,0:06:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N“Jacob had fallen in love with Rachel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.22,0:06:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“so he said: \N‘I am willing to serve you seven years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,for your younger daughter Rachel.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.66,0:06:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what’s the takeaway? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.86,0:06:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob didn’t marry \Nthe first person who came along, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.20,0:07:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe some pagan woman. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.20,0:07:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t say, \N‘Well, seven years is too long to wait. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.01,0:07:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to find some Philistine woman, \Nand I’ll marry her.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.28,0:07:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He was willing to wait \Nso that he could marry someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.81,0:07:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,who would join him \Nin the worship of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.28,0:07:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And you young folks, \Nif you are willing to wait, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.42,0:07:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be sure that you will have \NJehovah’s blessing as well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.26,0:07:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Jacob was apparently also \Na bit of a romantic. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.16,0:07:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice verse 20.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.60,0:07:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N“And Jacob served seven years for Rachel,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.10,0:07:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but notice this, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.10,0:07:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“but in his eyes \Nthey were like just a few days\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.97,0:07:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because of his love for her.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.44,0:07:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, isn’t that poetic? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.58,0:07:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob may have learned \Nto treasure his wife \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.55,0:07:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,by observing his parents, \NIsaac and Rebekah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.85,0:07:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears that they \Nhad a strong marriage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.02,0:07:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Just notice what we read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.05,0:07:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at Genesis 26:8, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.86,0:08:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis 26:8.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.73,0:08:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N“After some time had passed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.03,0:08:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“Abimelech king of the Philistines \Nwas looking out of the window, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.47,0:08:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and he saw Isaac,” \Nthat’s Jacob’s father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.94,0:08:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“displaying affection \Nfor Rebekah his wife.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.91,0:08:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So it appears \Nthat Isaac and Rebekah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.28,0:08:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,had a warm relationship, \Na good marriage.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.49,0:08:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what else \Ncan we learn about Jacob? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.16,0:08:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s an interesting detail recorded \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.26,0:08:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in chapter 25 and verse 27.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.33,0:08:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N“As the boys got bigger, Esau,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.57,0:08:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob’s brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.24,0:08:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“became a skilled hunter, \Na man of the field, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.44,0:08:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“but Jacob was a blameless man, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.41,0:08:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,dwelling in tents.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.51,0:08:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jacob liked to dwell in tents. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.72,0:08:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That might explain \Nthe strong bond that developed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,between Jacob and Joseph, \Nwho was his youngest for many years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.43,0:09:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now although Jacob \Nliked to dwell in tents, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.53,0:09:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,he was by no means a sissy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.90,0:09:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a strong man, \Nbut he was a spiritual man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.87,0:09:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s something \Nfor you young brothers to take away. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.14,0:09:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to be strong, \Nwe know you do, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.61,0:09:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but spirituality \Nshould come first.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.21,0:09:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, spiritual Jacob \Ngave his sons a beautiful lesson \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.19,0:09:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,on how to settle \Na difference with a family member. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We read about it \Nat Genesis chapter 32. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.19,0:09:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think all of us can learn \Nfrom his example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.56,0:09:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We learn at Genesis 32 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.57,0:09:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jacob’s brother, Esau, \Nwas coming to see him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.54,0:09:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they hadn’t seen \Neach other for 20 years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.74,0:09:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and to say that their parting \Nhad been difficult is an understatement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.18,0:09:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is that when they separated \Nmore than 20 years earlier, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.78,0:10:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Esau had vowed that one day \Nhe was going to kill his brother; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.22,0:10:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,now he was coming to see him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.72,0:10:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why was he \Nso angry with Jacob? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.43,0:10:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s because Jacob had received \Na blessing from their father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.13,0:10:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and Esau was not happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.57,0:10:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So Esau arrives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and 400 men are with him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.61,0:10:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why 400 men? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.84,0:10:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Bible doesn’t say. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.84,0:10:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But it could be \Nthat he was trying to show \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.85,0:10:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how important and prominent \Nhe had become. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.25,0:10:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jacob react? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.42,0:10:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he try to go tit for tat? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.02,0:10:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he try to show how important \Nand prominent he had become \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.16,0:10:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with all of the blessings \Nhe’d received? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.80,0:10:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he reopen old wounds? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.50,0:10:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he argue with his brother? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.13,0:10:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he say, \N‘You know I was right all along, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.10,0:10:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and you, Esau, \Nyou have been wrong’? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.74,0:11:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he demand an apology? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.78,0:11:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.78,0:11:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a lot that Jacob \Ncould have bragged about. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.41,0:11:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No question about that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.35,0:11:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no doubt that Jacob \Nhad Jehovah’s blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.92,0:11:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Early on, \Nwe read that an angel of Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.49,0:11:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,had appeared to him \Nand said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.56,0:11:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.59,0:11:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“the God of Abraham your father \Nand the God of Isaac. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.20,0:11:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“The land on which you are lying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.60,0:11:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“to you I am going to give it \Nand to your offspring. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.44,0:11:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am with you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I will safeguard you \Nwherever you go . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.88,0:11:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not leave you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.18,0:11:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s quite a blessing, \Nisn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.25,0:11:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.25,0:11:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,For a portion \Nof the previous night\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.35,0:11:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is, the night before Esau \Nand Jacob met up—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.16,0:11:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob had wrestled with an angel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.26,0:11:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a result, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.99,0:11:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he had managed \Nto receive another blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.33,0:11:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jacob didn’t flaunt \Nhis blessings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.70,0:12:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he humbled himself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he even bowed down \Nseven times before his brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.84,0:12:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of his wives \Nand his 11 sons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.05,0:12:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jacob settled \Nany lingering difference with Esau \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,not with his fists, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.95,0:12:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,not with a bragging tongue, \Nnot with a weapon, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.62,0:12:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but humbly, \Nlike a real man\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.59,0:12:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—like a real, spiritual man.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.40,0:12:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast, \Nhow did Jacob’s ten sons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.47,0:12:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,settle their difference \Nwith Joseph? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.47,0:12:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a bunch of cowards. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.51,0:12:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 10 to 1 \Nagainst Joseph. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.74,0:12:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,First, they decided \Nto kill their brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.35,0:12:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they delivered him \Nup into slavery. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.55,0:12:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Those jealous young men \Ndidn’t learn a thing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.02,0:12:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,from their father’s \Nexcellent spiritual example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.89,0:12:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you’re on the outs \Nwith a member of your family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.93,0:13:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if you had \Na serious difficulty with someone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.36,0:13:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,could you try to settle the matter \Npeacefully as Jacob did? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.07,0:13:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If the person tries to apologize, \Nbe gracious about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.41,0:13:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t make it difficult \Nfor him to apologize. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t dredge up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.81,0:13:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the unnecessary details \Nabout the past.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.98,0:13:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be in the right, \Nas Jacob was, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.95,0:13:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but isn’t the important thing \Nto make peace? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.05,0:13:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah loves the peacemakers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.46,0:13:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what else \Ndo we learn about Jacob? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.16,0:13:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We learn that he wasn’t \Nhis father’s favorite. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.66,0:13:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look \Nat Genesis chapter 25,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 28.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.87,0:13:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“And Isaac loved Esau \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.28,0:13:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“because it meant game in his mouth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.18,0:13:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whereas Rebekah loved Jacob.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this story may resonate \Nwith many of you out there, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.62,0:14:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,especially if you’ve grown up \Nin a large family\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.22,0:14:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or perhaps you’ve had \Na number of brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.06,0:14:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know \Nyour parents claim \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.33,0:14:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that they always treated \Nall of you the same, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.90,0:14:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that they never ever \Nhad a preference. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.23,0:14:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But ask the kids, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there anyone in the family \Nwho was the favorite? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.07,0:14:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They all know. \N‘She was!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.11,0:14:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They know this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.64,0:14:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The parents don’t realize it, \Nbut they are giving preferential treatment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this happens, \Nand it can be disconcerting at times.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.59,0:14:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine this scenario: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that you have a couple \Nwho have two children, two sons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.36,0:14:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One is a pioneer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.36,0:14:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He has never given his parents \Na moment’s grief. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.90,0:14:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The other \Nnever accepted the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.03,0:14:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but he has done well \Nin business, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.70,0:14:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a result, \Nhe has been generous to his parents, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.01,0:14:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and the parents are grateful, \Nvery grateful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.41,0:14:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the pioneer \Noften hears the parents bragging \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.85,0:15:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,about the successes \Nthat his brother has had in business. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.09,0:15:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the pioneer can’t help \Nthe parents materially very much, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.99,0:15:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and so he feels that there’s \Na bit of partiality there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.23,0:15:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it hurtful? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.23,0:15:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \NThat is life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.40,0:15:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s chemistry. \NIt’s just chemistry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.87,0:15:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But the pioneer needs to realize \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.30,0:15:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah God \Nappreciates his work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.94,0:15:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,His heavenly Father \Nloves him very much \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for the work \Nthat he is doing for His name.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.71,0:15:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Jacob must have known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.51,0:15:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that Isaac loved his brother \Nmore than he loved him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And perhaps he vowed \Nthat when he had children, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.45,0:15:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he would treat them all the same. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.46,0:15:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if he did, \Nhe didn’t keep that promise, did he? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.16,0:15:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone knew \Nthat Joseph was the favorite.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.93,0:15:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, have you noticed what we had to do \Nto make a composite of this family? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.10,0:15:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to read \Nfrom several different chapters of the Bible\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.91,0:16:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—Genesis 25, 26, 28, 29, 32. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.61,0:16:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can’t always get \Na complete picture of an incident \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.22,0:16:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,by reading just one chapter, \Njust by reading the chapter you are reading. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.62,0:16:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you have to extract details \Nfrom other chapters of the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.36,0:16:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s consider \None more example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.86,0:16:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,where getting the complete picture \Ncan enrich our understanding. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.40,0:16:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to be \Na shorter one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.40,0:16:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to consider \Nthe story of Naaman. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.37,0:16:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you remember the story. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.54,0:16:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,At 2 Kings 5:1, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.51,0:16:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we learn that Naaman \Nwas the chief of the army \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.31,0:16:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of Ben-hadad II, \Nthe king of Syria. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.05,0:16:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was a leper. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.08,0:16:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Ben-hadad learned \Nthat there was a prophet in Israel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Elisha who could heal him \Nof his leprosy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.69,0:16:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he told Naaman \Nthat he should go to Israel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.80,0:16:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and go to the prophet \Nand get healed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.43,0:16:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And so word was sent \Nto the king of Israel by letter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.40,0:17:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the king of Israel was asked \Nto send Naaman to Elisha. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.34,0:17:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when you think of it, \Nthis was a strange request \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.18,0:17:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because Israel and Syria \Nwere often at odds. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.01,0:17:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes there were \Nwars between them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.48,0:17:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and now, here you have \Nthe king of Syria sending his general, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.19,0:17:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the one who is going to head \Nthe army against Israel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.09,0:17:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and saying: ‘Well, I’d like my general \Nto be a more effective general. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.09,0:17:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please make sure \Nthat he gets healed?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.63,0:17:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, somehow, \Nhe’s sent to Elisha \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.73,0:17:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and Elisha kindly heals Naaman \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and Naaman becomes \Na worshipper of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.21,0:17:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we can imagine, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.21,0:17:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,remember we’re talking \Nabout using our imagination, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.84,0:17:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we can imagine \Nthat when Naaman returned to Syria, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.38,0:17:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ben-hadad had lots of nice things \Nto say about Elisha. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, everyone lived \Nhappily ever after, right? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.82,0:17:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If we didn’t read on, \Nwe might think so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.36,0:17:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But that’s not \Nthe end of the story. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.86,0:18:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In the next chapter, \Nchapter 6, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we learn that Ben-hadad \Ndeclared war against Israel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.34,0:18:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if Naaman \Nwas still the chief of the army, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.91,0:18:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,he’d be in an awkward position. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.08,0:18:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he going \Nto lead the armies of Syria \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.85,0:18:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,against fellow worshippers \Nof Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.62,0:18:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But it gets worse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.92,0:18:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ben-hadad learns that Elisha \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.82,0:18:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is revealing the Syrians’ war strategies \Nto the king of Israel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.13,0:18:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so he sends a large army \Nto capture Elisha\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.80,0:18:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,—the very man who \Nhad healed his general. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So much for gratitude. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.04,0:18:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s interesting \Nthat Naaman is not mentioned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.81,0:18:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as being at the head \Nof those armies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.54,0:18:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he get out of it somehow? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.64,0:18:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t ask me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.65,0:18:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If he’s resurrected, \Nyou’ll have to ask him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.35,0:18:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What lesson can we learn? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.59,0:19:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That the gratitude of the world \Nis fleeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.22,0:19:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of us may get excited \Nif there’s a favorable article \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.86,0:19:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah’s Witnesses \Nin a newspaper \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.36,0:19:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or if some TV personality \Nmakes a kind statement about us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.07,0:19:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But what did Jehovah God say? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.17,0:19:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis 3:15:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.20,0:19:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,, “I will put enmity \Nbetween you and the woman.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.24,0:19:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah’s organization \Nand Satan’s organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.74,0:19:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are always going to be at odds.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.71,0:19:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible reading isn’t a chore. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.75,0:19:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a joy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.75,0:19:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the whole picture \Nof what you’re reading, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.09,0:19:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ll enjoy it even more.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.36,0:19:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We wish you all \NJehovah’s rich blessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.16,0:19:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as you continue \Nto enhance your appreciation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.16,0:19:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for this sacred volume.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.53,0:19:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, let’s turn to Rocky. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.07,0:19:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Rocky \Nhas some practical application to share.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.61,0:19:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, and as David mentioned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.94,0:19:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a close connection between joy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.28,0:19:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and how we handle our Bible reading. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.61,0:20:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, \Nwe meet a pioneer sister \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.68,0:20:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,who did everything just right \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.75,0:20:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but still felt \Nthat her motivation was declining. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.62,0:20:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you pioneer or not, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.99,0:20:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,notice the importance \Nof properly digesting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.13,0:20:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our vital spiritual food.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.71,0:20:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s my roommate, Camille.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.45,0:20:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And, well, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.89,0:20:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.72,0:20:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven’t felt like myself recently. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.13,0:20:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I started regular pioneering \Na couple of years ago.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.30,0:20:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I was really zealous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.30,0:20:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But somewhere down the line, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.84,0:20:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost that good feeling. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.78,0:21:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, I was losing my joy \Nfor almost everything.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.86,0:21:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I honestly didn’t know \Nwhat was wrong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.20,0:21:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t like I was doing \Nanything bad.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.47,0:21:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.47,0:21:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Maybe I’m just tired.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.14,0:21:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn’t getting better. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.01,0:21:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to assess\Nwhat was going on with myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.98,0:21:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt love for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.12,0:21:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt love for the congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.72,0:21:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but I felt unmotivated in my service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.62,0:21:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like something was missing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.97,0:22:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As my enthusiasm waned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.68,0:22:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,my meeting attendance suffered too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.85,0:22:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thankfully, the loving elders \Nin my congregation noticed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.86,0:22:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and help was on the way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.40,0:22:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers visited \Nto see how I was doing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.17,0:22:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They really listened to me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.67,0:22:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and they asked about \Nmy spiritual routine.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.91,0:22:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I read the Bible every day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.85,0:22:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but, I admitted, \NI’m not a natural study person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.25,0:22:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They reminded me \Nabout the example of Mary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.12,0:22:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ mother.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.12,0:22:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I didn’t see the link, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.46,0:23:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but as we read from the Bible, \Nit became more clear.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.04,0:23:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary was known \Nfor being a faithful woman. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.95,0:23:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But what kept her faith strong?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.76,0:23:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible account said \Nthat Mary paid careful attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.79,0:23:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to words that had \Ndeep spiritual meaning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.00,0:23:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and later took time to meditate, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.80,0:23:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“drawing conclusions in her heart.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.24,0:23:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,By meditating on spiritual things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.58,0:23:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary strengthened her faith \Nand zeal for serving Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.96,0:24:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.89,0:24:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was reading spiritual food, \Nbut I wasn’t taking time to digest it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.16,0:24:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so it wasn’t sinking \Ndown into my heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.80,0:24:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, \NI was on a direct path \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.60,0:24:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to spiritual burnout \Nif I didn’t change something quick!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.34,0:24:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I began by taking control \Nof my busy schedule. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.28,0:24:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I made it a priority \Nto start my day with Bible reading. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.98,0:24:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I sought out quiet places \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.98,0:24:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,where I could meditate on what I read.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.15,0:24:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaningful Bible study reinvigorated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.22,0:24:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,my passion for serving Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.73,0:24:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and prayerful meditation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.80,0:24:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,helped me to refocus.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.67,0:24:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Over time, \Nmaking these changes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.91,0:24:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,helped me to find joy \Nin my service to Jehovah again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.72,0:25:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible says when we make time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.92,0:25:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to read and meditate on spiritual things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.59,0:25:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we will become \N“like a tree planted by streams of water,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.53,0:25:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with foliage that never withers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.73,0:25:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And everything we do will succeed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.18,0:25:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice that our sister \Nread the Bible every day? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.45,0:25:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But that alone did not give her \Nthe spiritual sustenance she needed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.85,0:25:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t want our Bible reading \Nto become an automatic process. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.92,0:25:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean\N—automatic process? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.93,0:25:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, breathing, walking, \Nor perhaps, riding a bicycle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.47,0:25:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,are things many can do \Nwithout even thinking. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.94,0:25:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They become automatic processes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.07,0:26:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To some extent, \Nthis is also true of reading.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.61,0:26:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what can help us \Ndevelop the art of meditation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.81,0:26:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When you finish reading a passage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.18,0:26:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you might pause \Nand ponder over what you have just read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.62,0:26:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to be sure \Nthat you understand it correctly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.76,0:26:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask yourself: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.76,0:26:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What does this \Nteach me about Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.96,0:26:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How can I apply this in my life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.23,0:26:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Or how can I use this \Nin my field ministry?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.17,0:26:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You should always make sure \Nto apply what you read. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.97,0:26:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And remember, \Nreading in a stress-free environment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.58,0:26:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with few distractions \Nhelps our concentration.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.38,0:26:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if our attention span is short \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.45,0:26:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and our mind starts to wander quickly? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.52,0:26:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting out with shorter study sessions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.19,0:26:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and gradually lengthening them \Nhave helped some. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.13,0:26:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal should be to linger in study, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.60,0:26:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,not to rush through it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.80,0:27:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s when our spiritual food \Nbecomes the refreshment we need.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.70,0:27:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Some excellent tools \Nwhen meditating are the illustrations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.31,0:27:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and photographs \Nwe find in our publications. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.71,0:27:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the Bible account \Nfound in Daniel chapter 5 as an example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.18,0:27:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It reads: “That very night \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.12,0:27:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Belshazzar \Nthe Chaldean king was killed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.56,0:27:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“And Darius the Mede \Nreceived the kingdom; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.03,0:27:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he was about 62 years old.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.56,0:27:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Using other scriptures \Nthat provide additional details, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.07,0:27:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,including prophecies about the event, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.07,0:27:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the Art Department \Nat world headquarters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.01,0:27:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,was able to paint a vivid picture \Nof what it may have been like that night, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.95,0:27:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,when the Medo-Persian soldiers \Nwaded through the Euphrates River \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.95,0:27:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and entered the city of Babylon \Nthrough its open gates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.99,0:27:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know that looking up \Nillustrations in our literature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.26,0:28:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,can be a helpful tool when meditating. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.33,0:28:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But why is that the case? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.06,0:28:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go behind the scenes \Nof the Art Department and find out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.61,0:28:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A visual aid often makes \Na clearer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.61,0:28:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or more lasting impression \Non the mind than does the spoken word.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.85,0:28:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the direction \Nof the Writing Committee, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.82,0:28:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the Art Department \Nhas enjoyed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.89,0:28:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the privilege of designing \Nand illustrating Bible literature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.09,0:28:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for almost 40 years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.56,0:28:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The department was established \Nsometime before 1976.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.30,0:28:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But a small team of artists \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.50,0:28:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,had been working \Non illustrations and typography \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.67,0:28:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from as far back \Nas the “Photo-Drama of Creation.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.48,0:28:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The work of publishing Bible literature \Nhas seen many changes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.39,0:29:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there are EPUBs, interactive PDFs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.56,0:29:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Web design, and HTML content, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.23,0:29:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,all of which require new skills\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.26,0:29:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as close collaboration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.43,0:29:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with many other Bethel departments.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.40,0:29:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The Art Department \Nis structured into teams. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.11,0:29:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Each team is made up \Nof designers, photographers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.91,0:29:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,illustrators, prop and set makers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.25,0:29:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,costume and makeup artists, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.08,0:29:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as production workers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.25,0:29:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The team lead and the scheduler \Nwork directly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.69,0:29:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Writing Department contact \Nknown as a compiler.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.89,0:29:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After receiving \Nan early version of the text, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.76,0:29:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the three brothers discuss \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.77,0:29:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose \Nand possible look of the design. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.97,0:29:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All on the team \Nare invited to collaborate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.74,0:29:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as concepts are developed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.71,0:29:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Each member contributes \Nto the overall design of a project.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.21,0:30:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Before any production work is started, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.42,0:30:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,concepts are sketched and developed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.99,0:30:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,These sketches become a blueprint \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.62,0:30:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that helps the team \Nunderstand the concept, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.29,0:30:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,plan the resources, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.30,0:30:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and ensure \Nthat the project stays on track.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.77,0:30:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the target audience? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.24,0:30:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How will this publication be used?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.91,0:30:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The design should be clear and simple. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.35,0:30:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it needs to work in all languages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.02,0:30:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no small task.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.83,0:30:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When the design is ready, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.16,0:30:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the compiler presents a mock-up \Nof the publication \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.43,0:30:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Writing Committee. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.43,0:30:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The committee reviews the design \Nand makes any needed adjustments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.87,0:31:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,After the concept is approved, \Nproduction begins.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.78,0:31:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Around the world, \Nthere are many photographers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.85,0:31:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who work part-time to assist \Nin providing images. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.32,0:31:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Photographs are also taken in our studio \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.46,0:31:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and other locations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.63,0:31:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,These images help give our publications \Nan international look.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.57,0:31:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Accuracy is vital. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.67,0:31:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A researcher provides \Nhistorical references and inspiration.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.14,0:31:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hair, makeup, and costumes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.38,0:31:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are designed to depict \Nthe time period and region.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.19,0:31:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Props, set design, and lighting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.76,0:31:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,provide the right look and setting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.89,0:31:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When combined, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.90,0:31:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,each element helps tell the story \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.23,0:31:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and capture the imagination of the viewer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.27,0:32:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sets are also built in 3D programs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.40,0:32:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They can be used as art source \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.94,0:32:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or as final illustrations.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.45,0:32:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether painted digitally \Nor with traditional materials, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.92,0:32:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the artist renders the illustration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.46,0:32:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in a style suited for its final use.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.27,0:32:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When design meets illustration, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.47,0:32:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,infographics are born.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.71,0:32:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,After final approval \Nby the Writing Committee, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.55,0:32:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,files are sent to the printeries \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.78,0:32:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to the website \Nor used to create other digital versions.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.09,0:32:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to reach the hearts of those \Nwho read a Bible-based publication, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.09,0:33:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,hands and hearts \Nhave to be involved in its creation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.73,0:33:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of us in the Art Department \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.07,0:33:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,consider it a privilege to give support \Nto the most urgent of all work\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.37,0:33:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—preaching the good news.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.19,0:33:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice \Nthe answer to our question, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.06,0:33:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can looking up illustrations \Nin our literature be helpful? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.86,0:33:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As the narrator said, “A visual aid \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.33,0:33:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“often makes a clearer \Nor more lasting impression on the mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.20,0:33:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,than does the spoken word.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.51,0:33:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But on top of that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.51,0:33:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,illustrations \Ncan help a story come alive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.85,0:33:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They help us \Nenvision an event before our eyes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.55,0:33:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and thus deepen our appreciation \Nfor Bible truths \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.29,0:34:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and ultimately for Jehovah God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.96,0:34:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,While illustrations and photographs \Ncan be a great complement, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.43,0:34:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s the written Word, God’s Word, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.76,0:34:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the source \Nof the spiritual food.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.23,0:34:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if we face a situation \Nin which we have access to nothing? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.74,0:34:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not allowed \Nto have a Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.58,0:34:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,no literature with illustrations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.18,0:34:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,no videos, \Nand no audio recordings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.68,0:34:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.78,0:34:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our recollection \Nof what we have read in the past \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.25,0:34:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,can keep our spirituality intact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.72,0:34:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,One of our brothers from Russia \Nfaced such a situation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.89,0:34:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what helped him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.34,0:34:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The year was 1963.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.97,0:34:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was 36 at the time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.44,0:35:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The KGB searched my home \Nand found some Bible literature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.21,0:35:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and some publishers’ field service reports. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.82,0:35:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was sentenced \Nto five years of imprisonment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.69,0:35:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for being an organizer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.19,0:35:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the third time \NI had been imprisoned.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.00,0:35:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Some brothers and sisters \Nand I went to the court \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.70,0:35:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to support Brother Vladimir. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.87,0:35:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When he saw us, \Nhe clasped his hands \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.57,0:35:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and declared, \N“Everything is fine!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.94,0:35:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A KGB officer told me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.11,0:35:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that the only reason \NI hadn’t been imprisoned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.65,0:35:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was because I had six children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.72,0:35:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But Vladimir was single.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.72,0:35:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just glad \Nthat they had arrested me and not him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.72,0:35:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I didn’t have a family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.90,0:35:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the camp, I didn’t have a Bible \Nor any Bible literature at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.13,0:35:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All I had to keep me going \Nwas the knowledge I already had.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.14,0:36:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We prayed for him, \Nand we sent greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.01,0:36:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and encouraging messages \Nto him through his relatives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.48,0:36:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to the strict censorship \Nin the camp,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.62,0:36:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we were not allowed \Nto write anything spiritual in our letters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.48,0:36:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to encourage each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.52,0:36:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we did, \Nthe letters were confiscated. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.43,0:36:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I really wanted to send Brother Mikhail \Nsomething encouraging. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.13,0:36:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was growing flowers \Nwith a group of inmates in the camp. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.87,0:36:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of a sending him a letter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.97,0:36:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to send him \Na bouquet of flowers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.18,0:36:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Vladimir’s sister Olga came to our home, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.38,0:36:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and she brought me a beautiful bouquet \Nof flowers from Vladimir. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.59,0:36:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t believe \Nthat I had received fresh flowers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.69,0:36:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from behind a barbed-wire fence\N—from inside the camp. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.03,0:36:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so touched \Nby his act of kindness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.60,0:37:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that my heart moved me \Nto write down some verses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.30,0:37:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a poem, \Nwhich I called “The Bouquet.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.61,0:37:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My relatives came \Nand visited me in the prison \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.88,0:37:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and delivered to me the poem. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.85,0:37:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept the poem \Nin a very secret place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.72,0:37:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It could have been confiscated, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.72,0:37:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could have been punished \Nbecause it was about God.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.43,0:37:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,After Vladimir was released from prison, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.43,0:37:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,well, he told me that my poem \Nhad really strengthened him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.50,0:37:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he had often taken it out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.63,0:37:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of its secret hiding place \Nto read it over and over again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.27,0:37:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If it hadn’t been for the support \NI received from Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.31,0:37:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the prayers of friends, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.31,0:37:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it would have been much harder \Nfor me to serve my time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.72,0:37:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The poem that I had received \Nhelped me not to feel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.15,0:37:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,separated from my friends \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.16,0:37:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and, most importantly, \Nfrom Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.66,0:38:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So many years have now gone by. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.26,0:38:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have remained firm \Nthrough the difficult times, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.73,0:38:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we continue serving Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.71,0:38:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately, Vladimir and I have been trying \Nto keep in touch by phone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.38,0:38:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but we haven’t seen each other \Nfor seven years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.11,0:38:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I would really love \Nto see Vladimir again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.75,0:38:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t know \Nthat I’ve decided to go and visit him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.32,0:38:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that he likes the surprise.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.16,0:39:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“I see these flowers, \Ngrown by hands\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.16,0:39:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hardened from work \Nthat prison demands.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.00,0:39:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“My friend has sent a bouquet.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.27,0:39:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“Prison three times \Nprevented our meeting,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.90,0:39:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“But you found a way \Nto convey a greeting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.71,0:39:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“My joy now moves me to say:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.64,0:39:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Greetings, my brother, \Nwith all of my heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.65,0:39:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You gave me strength, \Nalthough we’re apart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.78,0:39:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘While you have \Ncountless trials withstood,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.82,0:39:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You’ve strengthened me \Nas best you could.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.99,0:39:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Greetings, my friend \Non that narrow road,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.39,0:39:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You were always with me \Nthrough hardships untold.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.73,0:39:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘We worked so hard \Nfor spiritual treasure.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.90,0:39:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Blessed we were \Nfor sticking together.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.47,0:39:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Cruelly, my friend, \Nyou were taken from me\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.97,0:39:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘When they tried \Nto break our integrity.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.67,0:39:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘But God stood by us \Nand helped us to cope.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.11,0:40:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Conquer the evil, we did, \Nfor our dear Kingdom hope.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.38,0:40:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘How grateful we are \Nand always will be\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.82,0:40:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For spiritual vision \N by which we can see\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.12,0:40:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘The crown of life \Npromised to those\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.96,0:40:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Who stay on the loyal course \Nthey chose.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.33,0:40:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘How much you’ve endured, \Nlong-suffering friend.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.73,0:40:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘But Jehovah’s mercy \Nwill never end.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.74,0:40:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘On a paradise earth \Nour hands will unite,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.84,0:40:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Planting more flowers \Nto gladden His sight.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.34,0:40:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Christ Jesus will heal us \Nduring his reign,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.01,0:40:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘So no trace of sin \Nwill ever remain.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.25,0:40:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And far from the trials \Nthat we overcame,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.05,0:40:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever we’ll praise \NJehovah’s great name!’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.90,0:40:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,True friends are such a blessing \Nfrom Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.90,0:40:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don’t really know \Nwho they are until disaster strikes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.54,0:41:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,During my whole life, \Nwalking in the way of the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.95,0:41:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I have often thought \Nabout the words of Psalm 119:63, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.85,0:41:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,where it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.45,0:41:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am a friend of all who fear you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.95,0:41:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and of those who keep your orders.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.46,0:41:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Our serving side by side \Nin the Kingdom work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.03,0:41:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,has strengthened our friendship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.90,0:41:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is only that sort of friendship \Nthat will last forever!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.88,0:41:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful friendship! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.25,0:41:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brotherhood truly is \Na blessing from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.98,0:41:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Mikhail Savitsky spent many years \Nas a circuit overseer,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.86,0:41:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,helping the Kingdom work progress \Nin Siberia, northern Caucasus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.26,0:41:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the countries \Nof Georgia and Armenia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.53,0:42:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1992, he had the privilege \Nof being one of those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.23,0:42:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who signed the documents that confirmed \Nlegal recognition of our work in Russia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.41,0:42:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we regret to inform you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.01,0:42:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that some time \Nafter this segment was produced, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.08,0:42:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Vladimir Varkholik \Nfell asleep in death. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.78,0:42:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He was 88 years old \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.79,0:42:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and had served Jehovah faithfully \Nfor over 59 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.66,0:42:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of his death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.66,0:42:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,he had served as a pioneer \Nfor some 26 years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.89,0:42:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and as an elder \Nin the congregation for 43 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.60,0:42:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,From his interview, \Nyou can clearly see the faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.70,0:42:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that kept his spirituality strong \Nthrough 12 years of imprisonment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.67,0:42:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And he is a good example for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.18,0:42:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice one aspect \Nof his circumstances while incarcerated? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.15,0:42:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.22,0:42:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the camp, \NI didn’t have a Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.42,0:42:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“or any Bible literature at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.76,0:42:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“All I had to keep me going \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.06,0:43:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,was the knowledge I already had.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.46,0:43:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That could happen to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.70,0:43:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When persecution starts, \Nwe need to be prepared. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.30,0:43:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s one reason \Nwhy it is so important \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.67,0:43:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,not to neglect \Nour study of the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.17,0:43:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,while we have the opportunity.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.24,0:43:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, back to David.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.68,0:43:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Rocky. \NWe’re truly sorry to hear about Vladimir. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.05,0:43:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But one thing is certain, \Nwe know that Jehovah God will not forget \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.39,0:43:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the love that he showed for His name. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.79,0:43:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a moving interview indeed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.16,0:43:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, back in June, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.16,0:43:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a number of new Kingdom songs \Nwere released electronically, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.37,0:43:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but one was missing—number 151. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.31,0:43:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you noticed that, didn’t you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.44,0:43:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you did because nothing escapes \Nthe eagle eyes of you brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.45,0:43:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here it is, number 151. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.58,0:43:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s entitled \N“The Revealing of God’s Sons.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.22,0:44:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And it reminds us \Nthat the time is getting near \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.16,0:44:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,when the anointed \Nwill hear the final call. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.43,0:44:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s listen.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.04,0:44:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The time is near when God reveals\NHis faithful chosen ones.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.91,0:44:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In heaven they will rule with Christ\NAs mighty spirit sons.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.22,0:44:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The sons of God will be revealed\NAlong with Christ, their Lord.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.10,0:44:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll join him in his victory\NAnd share in his reward.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.54,0:45:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And soon the last remaining ones\NWill hear his final call.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.52,0:45:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The King of kings and Lord of lords\NWill then collect them all.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.90,0:45:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The sons of God will be revealed\NAlong with Christ, their Lord.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.91,0:45:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll join him in his victory\NAnd share in his reward.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.25,0:45:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then with Christ, these sons of God\NWill wage the final war.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.19,0:45:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The joyous marriage to the Lamb\NWill last forevermore.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.70,0:46:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The sons of God will be revealed\NAlong with Christ, their Lord.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.75,0:46:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll join him in his victory\NAnd share in his reward.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.93,0:46:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you think that was \Na beautiful song, Rocky?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.16,0:46:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.16,0:46:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That was one beautiful song. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.36,0:46:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I really do appreciate \Nthe Watchtower chorus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.77,0:46:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Only two or three of them \Nhave professional training, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.64,0:46:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rest have got where they are \Njust through hard work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.04,0:46:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is something \Nthat all of us can keep in mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.84,0:46:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Practice, practice, practice singing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.85,0:46:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you \Nget to the Kingdom Hall, sing out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.52,0:46:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s a very timely song, \Nconsidering how close we are to the end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.12,0:46:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m sure all of you agree that the closer\Nwe are to the end of this system of things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.86,0:46:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the more work there is \Nin the field ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.00,0:47:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are individuals whom we \Nrarely find home due to their secular work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.00,0:47:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In Europe, our brothers \Nand sisters have found a way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.87,0:47:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach one such group.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.28,0:47:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year, thousands of truck drivers \Nfrom all over the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.72,0:47:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,crisscross the European continent.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.86,0:47:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They work hard to make ends meet \Nfor their families \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.20,0:47:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but often have to spend \Nweeks away from home.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.70,0:47:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus and his apostles \Napproached people wherever they were. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.84,0:47:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It is this same spirit \Nthat must motivate us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.81,0:47:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,By trying to reach truck drivers \Nwherever they can be found, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.48,0:47:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we can make sure \Nthat everyone receives a witness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.85,0:47:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,even those who would \Notherwise be missed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.32,0:47:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in the Rotterdam area \Nwhich has a lot of truck traffic. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.19,0:47:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We cover our regular territory \Nonce every three months, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.29,0:48:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,while these truck drivers \Nare hardly ever reached.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.10,0:48:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We noticed that 300,000 trucks \Ncrossed France every year. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.83,0:48:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, it was necessary to explore \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.30,0:48:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this formidable potential for the ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.34,0:48:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Many truck drivers use truck stops \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.41,0:48:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to take a short break\Nor even spend the night there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.21,0:48:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s ideal for preaching.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.22,0:48:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,While we are parked here, resting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.42,0:48:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we are cleaning the trucks; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.73,0:48:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we are washing our clothes \Nbecause there is no laundry here; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.66,0:48:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and also we do our cooking.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.40,0:48:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,One day on my way to France, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.87,0:48:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to stop in Austria \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.54,0:48:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to swap drivers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.21,0:48:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My colleague went to the bathroom, \Nand I was alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.12,0:49:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, a Witness came \Nand offered me a magazine.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.62,0:49:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Much effort is being put into reaching \Ntruck drivers in an organized way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.90,0:49:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We made sure all truck stops \Nwere mapped \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.93,0:49:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and organized schedules so that pioneers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.67,0:49:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,can preach in this territory \Nat least once a day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.37,0:49:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Publishers will encounter \Nmany different nationalities and languages.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.38,0:49:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The language barrier \Nis one of the biggest challenges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.88,0:49:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,On any given morning, \Nyou can encounter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.92,0:49:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,up to ten different languages: \NRomanian, Russian, Polish.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.16,0:49:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When I looked at the magazine, \NI saw that it was a Watchtower, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.59,0:49:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but I thought it was in German. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.63,0:49:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I told this brother \Nthat I did not speak German. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.13,0:49:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he had a look at my license plate \Nand saw that it was Romanian. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.47,0:49:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He again offered me \Nthe magazine and told me: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.07,0:49:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is Romanian. \NIt is for you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.18,0:49:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw it, \NI was very happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.31,0:50:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I took the magazine \Nand was very glad.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.35,0:50:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we don’t speak in tongues \Nlike the first-century Christians did. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.62,0:50:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But jw.org makes us feel like \Nwe can preach in any language.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.80,0:50:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to go further \Nthan just distributing publications. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.70,0:50:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to be real teachers, \Nand to do that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.64,0:50:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we can make use of the videos.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.58,0:50:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A driver had his Bible \Nwide open on his dashboard \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.28,0:50:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and literally cried when he watched \Nthe video Why Study the Bible?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.46,0:50:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Since truck drivers spend \Nmost of their time on the road, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.43,0:50:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a real challenge to follow up \Non those who have shown any interest.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.17,0:50:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s very difficult to do return visits \Nor to start Bible studies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.77,0:50:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don’t know when you will meet \Na truck driver again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.84,0:51:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we try to get their e-mail addresses \Nas soon as possible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.95,0:51:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The results were remarkable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.68,0:51:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in the last service year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.69,0:51:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,about 100,000 magazines were placed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.29,0:51:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,100 Bible studies were started, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.26,0:51:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and 4,000 videos were shown.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.43,0:51:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience shows \Nthat even if it’s not possible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.67,0:51:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to obtain an e-mail address, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.67,0:51:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the slightest witness given \Ncan have a great impact.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.34,0:51:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, I returned to Romania. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.21,0:51:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I started a Bible study, \Nprogressed spiritually, got married, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.08,0:51:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and now I am \Nan unbaptized publisher. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.35,0:51:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The brother that first \Ncontacted me has no idea.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.12,0:51:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrews 6:11 invites us all \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.73,0:51:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘to show industriousness’ in our ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.00,0:51:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you invest in \Nthis form of ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.07,0:52:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the more fulfillment you get \Nfrom the positive response of the drivers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.41,0:52:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a good thing \Nto preach the good news at truck stops \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.81,0:52:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because all drivers need to feel God’s love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.35,0:52:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to see that God really cares for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.08,0:52:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And like me, \Nthey can make changes in their lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.56,0:52:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And they need to see that Jehovah \N has promised a future paradise \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.13,0:52:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and how this will affect them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.20,0:52:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and their families.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.17,0:52:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What great results \Ncame from this preaching initiative, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.77,0:52:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and what a delight to see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.84,0:52:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,how many of the publishers \Nused our videos while witnessing! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.71,0:52:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Although videos can be great tools, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.72,0:52:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we all must continue \Nto develop our teaching skills \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.19,0:52:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and our ability to reason \Nfrom the Scriptures. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.52,0:53:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers witnessing \Nat truck stops did just that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.79,0:53:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the results \Nspeak for themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.00,0:53:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be happy to know that one \Nof the truck drivers who was interviewed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.00,0:53:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ion Bolbotina from Romania \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.60,0:53:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,was recently baptized \Nas one of Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.71,0:53:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It is beautiful \Nto see how our efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.84,0:53:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ministry \Nare blessed by Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.51,0:53:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Margarita Königer has seen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.52,0:53:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the growth of the Kingdom work \Nall her life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.19,0:53:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,She has served \Nas a missionary since 1966, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.12,0:53:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and we met her in Hungary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.19,0:53:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where she has now served \Nfor about nine years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.03,0:59:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 50 years \Nsince she graduated from Gilead, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.30,0:59:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Königer has learned \Nseven languages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.70,0:59:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and has served \Nin five different countries. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.61,0:59:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And recently, \Nshe received a new assignment\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.91,0:59:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,—the Chinese field \Nin Munich, Germany. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.41,0:59:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Daily reading \Nand meditating on God’s Word, the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.68,0:59:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,has given her \Nthe strength she needs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.29,0:59:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue with joy \Nin her missionary assignment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.83,0:59:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The same is important \Nif you’re young. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.63,0:59:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking the time \Nto properly digest spiritual food, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.03,0:59:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,by enhancing your Bible reading, \Ncan teach you to make good decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.97,0:59:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nwhom should you choose as friends? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.91,0:59:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay special attention to this music video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.75,1:00:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,entitled Where I Belong, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.95,1:00:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which will help you choose \Nthe best friends possible.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.53,1:00:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now everyone, it seems to me,\NKnows just the place he wants to be.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.27,1:00:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what’s right; I know what’s wrong;\NAnd, yes, I know where I belong.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.11,1:00:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels so good, so good to know\NWhere I should be, where I should go\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.12,1:00:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To find good friends and company\NWho build me up and care for me.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.97,1:01:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, here in my heart \NThe feelings are strong.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.41,1:01:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, it’s you \NWho’ll help me get through\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.59,1:01:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And show me where I belong.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.60,1:01:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My heart is sure, it’s clear to me,\NI’m standing where I want to be.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.85,1:01:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I read God’s Word. I make it live.\NIt moves my heart. What can I give?\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.72,1:01:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I know; yes, now I see\NWhere real friends are; that’s where I’ll be.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.30,1:02:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re all I want; they’re family;\NJehovah’s gift with love to me.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.91,1:02:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, here in my heart\NThe feelings are strong.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.18,1:02:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, it’s you\NWho’ll help me get through\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.09,1:02:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And show me where I belong.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.31,1:02:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What a fine young man! \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.38,1:02:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And he made the right decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.85,1:02:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He decided he belongs \Nin Jehovah’s organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.72,1:02:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And did you notice his habit? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.05,1:02:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He read the Bible regularly, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.22,1:03:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,brought it with him on the trip, \Nmeditated about what he read\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.89,1:03:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—both after reading \Nand also when out in the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.03,1:03:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He took the time to grasp \Nthe wonders of Jehovah’s creation, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.84,1:03:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and we need to do the same. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.51,1:03:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to enhance our Bible reading\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.58,1:03:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,—visualize what we read \Nand try to get the whole picture. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.38,1:03:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the organization \Nhas given us many fine tools \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.49,1:03:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to visualize our Bible reading, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.62,1:03:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,such as the illustrations \Nin our publications, audio dramas, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.43,1:03:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and dramatic Bible readings \Nand videos. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.76,1:03:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Make full use of them, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.30,1:03:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and meditate about what you learn.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.77,1:03:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Rocky, \NI agree with everything you’ve said. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.47,1:03:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as of September the 1st, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.21,1:03:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,members of the Bethel family \Nhave been moving \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.08,1:03:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,from Brooklyn to our new headquarters \Nat Warwick, New York. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.92,1:04:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you’re listening in from Britain, \Nthat’s Warwick to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.99,1:04:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Warwick or Warwick, it’s the same place. \NTomato, tomato. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.32,1:04:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re very, \Nvery happy about this move. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.33,1:04:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a tremendous project \Nto move the entire Bethel family \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.06,1:04:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,from Brooklyn to Warwick, \Nand it’s going to take some time. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.14,1:04:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know you’re anxious \Nto see the property in person, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.57,1:04:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’re not going to be able \Nto get the property ready for tours \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.51,1:04:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,until April 3, 2017, that’s a Monday. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.18,1:04:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to repeat that. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.18,1:04:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not going to be able \Nto open for tours \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.85,1:04:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,until Monday, April 3, 2017. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.39,1:04:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you \Nhappen to be touring Wallkill \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.76,1:04:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or Patterson between now and then, \Nit’s going to be a mighty temptation \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.63,1:04:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for you to tiptoe \Nup to the property line in Warwick, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.64,1:04:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps put some twigs \Nand branches in your hat, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.17,1:04:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,climb a tree, \Nand see what you can see. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.01,1:04:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, don’t do it. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.01,1:05:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re working very hard \Nto get everything ready for you. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.41,1:05:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We want everything to be just right \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.95,1:05:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,when the facility is open for tours. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.09,1:05:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And here’s another interesting thing: \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.12,1:05:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You are going to be able \Nto go online \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.12,1:05:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and schedule a tour. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.46,1:05:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And so arrangements are being made \Nwith the congregations and the branches \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.66,1:05:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they’re going to be able \Nto do that. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.93,1:05:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you’ll be able to avoid the rush.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.20,1:05:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We also wanted to take the opportunity \Nto mention that two new interviews \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.47,1:05:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Viewpoints on the Origin of Life \Nvideo series \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.81,1:05:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,have now been posted. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.81,1:05:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You may remember this series \Nfrom the April program. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.08,1:05:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s about scientists \Nwho have concluded \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.42,1:05:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that life did not come about \Nby chance, but by design. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.69,1:05:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You will find these new interviews \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.83,1:05:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the “Interviews and Experiences” \Ncategory, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.36,1:05:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,under the “Origins of Life” heading.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.87,1:05:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d like to conclude \Nwith these greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.44,1:06:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from northeastern Bolivia, \Nin a region called Beni. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.41,1:06:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This area has a publisher ratio \Nof 1 Witness to 426 people. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.15,1:06:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Their territory consists \Nmainly of rivers and jungles. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.88,1:06:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The approximately 350 publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.02,1:06:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in the cities of Riberalta \Nand Guayaramerín \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.82,1:06:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,need to be innovative to reach \Nall corners of their territory. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.29,1:06:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.30,1:06:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,under the direction of the local branch, \Na Witness pilot \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.80,1:06:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,flies brothers to isolated populations. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.90,1:06:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In other cases, some communities \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.14,1:06:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,located on the banks of rivers \Nare reachable \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.61,1:06:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,only by boat. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.61,1:06:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, preaching trips by boat \Nare arranged from time to time. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.31,1:06:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Some trips last well over a month. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.48,1:06:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But some parts of the territory \Ncan be reached by motorcycle. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.12,1:06:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers and sisters travel \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.32,1:06:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,up to four hours \Nto cover such territories.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.69,1:06:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers and sisters in Beni \Nsend their warm love, and so do we, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.63,1:07:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to all of you around the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.90,1:07:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Rocky, I’d like to thank you for doing \Nthe heavy lifting for me during this program.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.54,1:07:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re a good brother, \Nyou know that?\N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.28,1:07:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My privilege.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.28,1:07:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s a good brother. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.41,1:07:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is JW Broadcasting \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.08,1:07:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in Brooklyn, New York.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.32,0:00:02.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さん ようこそ! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.95,0:00:05.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒できることを\N嬉しく思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.32,0:00:09.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,新たな奉仕年度 そして\N新たなマンスリープログラムです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.03,0:00:12.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,共に司会をするのは \Nセス・ハイアット兄弟です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.46,0:00:14.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロッキーとも呼ばれていますね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.10,0:00:17.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロッキー\Nどんなプログラムを楽しめますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.43,0:00:21.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教奉仕における喜びを\N失いそうになっている—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.74,0:00:24.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,一人の姉妹のドラマがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.91,0:00:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が必要でしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.11,0:00:31.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に実際的な内容から\N益を得られます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.41,0:00:36.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに 世界本部のアート部門に関する\N素晴らしいビデオもあります \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.42,0:00:38.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が行われていますか？ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.12,0:00:40.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,益を得るために何ができますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.42,0:00:42.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,その答えが得られます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.86,0:00:47.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨーロッパではトラックの駐車場で\N証言がなされています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.96,0:00:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは 家から離れて暮らす\N人々に達する点で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.04,0:00:55.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に産出的な奉仕といえます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.37,0:01:00.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めてご覧の皆さんも\Nいつもご覧の皆さんもようこそ！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.91,0:01:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,9月の JW Broadcastingです!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.60,0:01:30.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんは「信仰に倣う」の本の\N研究を楽しんでおられますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.27,0:01:32.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい本ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.61,0:01:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,特に 序章に心を\N引き付けられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.18,0:01:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこでは 想像力を働かせるよう\N励まされています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.29,0:01:46.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな光景が見え\Nどんな音が聞こえ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.12,0:01:52.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな匂いがするか想像し \N登場人物の気持ちを感じ取るのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.76,0:01:55.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 考えすぎるのは\N良くありませんが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.73,0:02:00.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでいることをしっかりと\N思い描くのは大切なことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.60,0:02:04.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日は そのことについて\Nお話したいと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.24,0:02:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読む際には\N全体像をつかみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.35,0:02:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,例として よく知られた聖書の記述を\N取り上げてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.79,0:02:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ステップファミリーの中で\N育った経験がありますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.26,0:02:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうであれば ヤコブの子である\Nヨセフと共通点があるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.90,0:02:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨセフは 10人の異母兄弟を含む\N大きな家族で育ちました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.37,0:02:40.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,これを 一つの集合体として\Nとらえてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.31,0:02:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,お互いにどのような影響を\N及ぼしたのかを考えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.18,0:02:48.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族の一人一人について—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.32,0:02:50.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,その特徴などを書き出すところからー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.49,0:02:53.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,始めることができるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.72,0:02:57.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨセフや 彼の異母兄弟に\Nついてはどうですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.39,0:02:59.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなことを知っていますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.63,0:03:07.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダ シメオン レビ ダン ナフタリに\Nついて考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らの特徴などを書き出し\Nお互いの関係について考えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.34,0:03:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書に記録されている出来事を\N読むときには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.25,0:03:19.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある人の行動はー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.98,0:03:22.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人にも影響を与えるということを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.29,0:03:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,忘れないようにしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.76,0:03:28.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで何かの出来事を読むときには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.73,0:03:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,影響を受けた人についても考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.13,0:03:34.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,例を挙げましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.16,0:03:37.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記には ヤコブの息子ルベンが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.47,0:03:40.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビルハと性的な不道徳を犯したことがー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.90,0:03:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,記録されています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.57,0:03:47.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,周囲の人々にも影響が\N及んだことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.14,0:03:49.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ルベンはどんな人でしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.15,0:03:51.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,レアが最初に生んだ子です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:53.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではビルハとは誰ですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.85,0:03:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラケルの侍女です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.89,0:04:01.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,レアとラケルの結婚生活の\N始まりについて考えると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.69,0:04:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,二人の間には 幾らかの対立や緊張が\Nあったとは考えられませんか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.10,0:04:08.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと そうだったでしょう \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.97,0:04:13.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに 母親の態度は\Nその息子たちの態度にも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.20,0:04:16.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,何らかの影響を与えるものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.01,0:04:19.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうしたことすべてを\N考慮に入れましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.18,0:04:21.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビルハには二人の息子がいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.81,0:04:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダンとナフタリです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.95,0:04:29.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 年長の異母兄弟が\N自分の母親と淫行を犯したと聞いて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.15,0:04:31.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,どう感じたでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.92,0:04:34.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,緊張が走ったに違いありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.29,0:04:40.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ひとつの集合体として家族をとらえると\Nこうしたことがわかってきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:44.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて ヨセフが17歳のときー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.63,0:04:48.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,10人の異母兄弟は\N幾つくらいでしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.30,0:04:49.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,30歳ぐらいでー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.77,0:04:52.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の父親にもなれるくらいでしょうか？ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.98,0:04:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうではありません \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.31,0:04:58.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際には ヨセフと年長のルベンとはー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.51,0:05:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わずか 7歳しか離れていません \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.52,0:05:06.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブの息子のうち11人は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.29,0:05:08.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼がラバンのために働いたー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,7年のうちに生まれています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:17.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうして7年間に11人も\N生まれたのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.67,0:05:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,答えは簡単です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.47,0:05:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブには二人の妻と\N二人のそばめがいたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.21,0:05:27.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 次の出産までに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.34,0:05:31.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,9か月待たなければならない\Nということはなかったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.95,0:05:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際 同じ年に生まれた \N同い年の息子たちもいたことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.42,0:05:41.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで ヨセフが売られた\N17歳のとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.26,0:05:44.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,年長の息子は24歳でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.63,0:05:47.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,一つか二つしか年の離れていないー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.36,0:05:49.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の異母兄弟もいたことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:52.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから それは10代後半からー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.64,0:05:55.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,20代前半の若者のグループでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:05:58.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう考えると 幾人かの息子がー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.07,0:06:01.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,感情的な反応を見せたのもうなずけます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.91,0:06:04.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,息子たちについて理解できました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.31,0:06:06.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 父親のヤコブはどうですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:08.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,何を学べるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.42,0:06:10.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,沢山あります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.12,0:06:13.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,一つの点として\N彼は霊的な人でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.32,0:06:19.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは 結婚を真剣に考える\N兄弟姉妹にとって参考になるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.10,0:06:22.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは エホバとの良い関係を\N保つために—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.43,0:06:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あらゆる努力を払いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.37,0:06:31.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記 29章18節を\N例として取り上げましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.44,0:06:34.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,お読みしますので\N画面をご覧ください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.71,0:06:37.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚という観点で読みましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.11,0:06:40.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記 29章18節です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.68,0:06:42.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.05,0:06:44.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ヤコブはラケルを愛していた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.22,0:06:48.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それで彼は言った\N「あなたの下の娘ラケルのため—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.26,0:06:52.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは喜んで\N あなたに七年仕えます」”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.70,0:06:53.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブはー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.80,0:06:56.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,それが異教徒であろうと構わず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.17,0:07:00.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初に出会う女性と結婚するという\Nことはありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.14,0:07:01.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,“7年も 待てない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.34,0:07:04.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,“フィリステア人の女性を見つけて\N結婚しよう”などとも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.84,0:07:06.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,言いませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを共に崇拝できる人と\N結婚するため喜んで待ったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.25,0:07:16.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い皆さんも\N待つ態度を示すなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.42,0:07:20.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じようにエホバの祝福を\N確信できるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.56,0:07:24.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは ロマンチックな人でも\Nあったようです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.13,0:07:26.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,20節に こうあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.50,0:07:31.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,”こうしてヤコブはラケルのために\N 七年間仕えたが—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.83,0:07:33.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,次に注目してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.50,0:07:39.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,”彼女に対する愛ゆえに\N それは彼の目にほんの数日のようであった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.14,0:07:41.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩的ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.88,0:07:48.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは 親のイサクやリベカを見て\N妻を慈しむことを学んだでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.28,0:07:51.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,二人の結婚の絆は強固でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことは 創世記 26章8節から\N明らかです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.13,0:08:02.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記 26章8節です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.67,0:08:06.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,“彼のそこでの日数が\N 延びているときのこと—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.57,0:08:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“フィリスティア人の王アビメレクが\N 窓から外を見て眺めていると—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.04,0:08:18.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そこではイサクが妻のリベカと\N 楽しく過ごしているのであった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.92,0:08:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,明らかにイサクとリベカは\N温かな結婚の絆で結ばれていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.26,0:08:29.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに ヤコブから\N何を学べますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.66,0:08:35.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,25章27節からも\N興味深い情報を得られます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.97,0:08:37.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.30,0:08:40.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,“さて 男の子たちは\N 大きくなってゆき—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.27,0:08:45.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,“[兄の]エサウは狩りの仕方を知る人\N 野の人となったが—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.58,0:08:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ヤコブはとがめのない人で\N 天幕に住んでいた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.08,0:08:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは 天幕で過ごすのを好みました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.05,0:09:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブが 末息子のヨセフと\N深い絆を育んだ様子が理解できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.49,0:09:07.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 天幕を好んだからといって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:10.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは弱々しい人では\Nありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.63,0:09:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は 強く 何より霊的な人でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.57,0:09:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い人も 見倣えますね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.27,0:09:20.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,強い人でありたいと思うでしょう \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもまず 霊的な人であるべきです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.11,0:09:27.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるとき 霊的な人ヤコブは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.05,0:09:31.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族の中で生じる問題を\N解決する方法について—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.22,0:09:34.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,息子たちに素晴らしい\N教訓を与えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.76,0:09:38.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 創世記 32章に\N記録されています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.49,0:09:41.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちすべては\Nその手本から学べます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.70,0:09:44.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記 32章を見るとー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.20,0:09:47.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブの兄弟エサウが\N会いにやってきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.70,0:09:50.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に難しい問題があったため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.04,0:09:53.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らは20年も顔を\N合わせていませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.64,0:09:58.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際には20年以上前に \N彼らは関係を断ちましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.91,0:10:04.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,エサウは いつか弟のヤコブを\N殺すと誓っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.15,0:10:07.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのエサウが会いに来たのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.19,0:10:11.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ それほどの怒りを\Nヤコブに抱いていたのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.23,0:10:15.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは ヤコブが父親の祝福を\N受けたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.50,0:10:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エサウは 気に入りませんでした \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.00,0:10:22.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのエサウが 400人のもの男たちを\N引き連れて到着しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.57,0:10:23.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜでしょうか？ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.97,0:10:26.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は何も述べていません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.54,0:10:30.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,重んじられ 際立った存在になった\Nということを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.11,0:10:33.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,示すためだったかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.92,0:10:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは どのように\N反応しましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.22,0:10:39.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,いわば しっぺ返しをして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.06,0:10:42.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,受けた祝福により\N自分がどれほど重んじられ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.29,0:10:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,際立った存在になったかを\N示したでしょうか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.43,0:10:49.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,古傷を暴いたでしょうか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.77,0:10:51.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,議論をしましたか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.83,0:10:54.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは最初から正しかった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.04,0:10:56.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,“間違っていたのは\N あなたの方ですよね？”などと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.94,0:10:58.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,言いましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.31,0:11:01.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,謝罪を求めたでしょうか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.18,0:11:02.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.88,0:11:05.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブには誇れることが\Nたくさんありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.82,0:11:07.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,疑問の余地はありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.38,0:11:11.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,疑いなく ヤコブは\Nエホバの祝福を受けていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.82,0:11:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのみ使いが彼に表われて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.12,0:11:17.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは あなたの父—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.39,0:11:21.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,“アブラハムの神\N イサクの神エホバである”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:23.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたの横たわっている地—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.43,0:11:27.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしはそれをあなたに\N そしてあなたの胤に与える”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.34,0:11:29.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしはあなたと共におり—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.97,0:11:33.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,“その行くすべての道で\N あなたを守り—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.38,0:11:36.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは……あなたを\N 離れないからである”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.41,0:11:38.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい祝福です \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:41.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし それだけでは\Nありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.18,0:11:45.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブがエサウと会う \N前の晩のこと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.92,0:11:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブはみ使いと格闘しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.19,0:11:54.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして結果として 更に祝福を\N受けることになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.03,0:11:59.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもヤコブは そうした祝福を\N見せびらかしたりしませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.03,0:12:02.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,むしろ 謙遜に振る舞いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.30,0:12:07.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際ヤコブは 妻たちや\N11人の息子たちの前で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.81,0:12:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エサウに 七回も\N身をかがめたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.05,0:12:17.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは エサウとの間の深い溝を\N力によってでも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.22,0:12:22.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,自慢することによってでも\N戦いの武器によってでもなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.36,0:12:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的な人として\N謙遜な仕方で解決したのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.50,0:12:32.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,それとは対照的に\N彼の10人の息子たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:35.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように問題を\N解決したでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:40.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,臆病にも 10人でヨセフひとりを\N相手にしたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初は 彼を殺そうとしましたが\N結局は奴隷として売りました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.32,0:12:49.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみに満たされた若者たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.15,0:12:51.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,父親の素晴らしい霊的な手本からー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.92,0:12:54.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,何も学んでいませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.72,0:12:57.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしあなたが 家族の中でー \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.09,0:12:59.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰かとの関係を損ねていたり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.83,0:13:02.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,深刻な違いを抱えているなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.50,0:13:05.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブのように平和な仕方でー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.07,0:13:07.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題を解決しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.04,0:13:09.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし相手が謝ろうとしているならー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.37,0:13:11.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,広い心で接し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.11,0:13:14.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,謝りにくい状況を\N作らないようにします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.68,0:13:19.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,過去に生じた些細なことを\N持ち出さないにしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.08,0:13:22.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブのように\Nあなたの方が正しかったとしても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.82,0:13:25.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,重要なのは\N平和を生み出すことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.86,0:13:29.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは 平和を作り出す人を\N喜ばれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.86,0:13:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,他にも ヤコブから何を学べますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.66,0:13:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は 父親のお気に入りという訳では\Nなかったことがわかります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.84,0:13:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記 25章28節を見てみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.07,0:13:48.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そしてイサクはエサウを愛していた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.58,0:13:52.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,“その口に獲物を\N もたらしたからであった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.11,0:13:55.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかしリベカは\N ヤコブを愛する者であった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.95,0:13:58.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし皆さんが 大きな家族の中で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.49,0:14:02.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,大勢の兄弟姉妹に囲まれて\N成長してきたとすれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.79,0:14:05.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,この状況を\Nよく理解できるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.56,0:14:10.03,Default2,,0,0,0,, 皆さんのご両親は\N“どの子も公平に扱っている—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.03,0:14:12.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,“えこひいきなどしない”\N と言うでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.43,0:14:14.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも子どもたちに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.07,0:14:17.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,“誰か親に気に入られている子がいるか？”\N と尋ねれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.54,0:14:21.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっとみんな知っていて\N“あの子！”と答えるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.01,0:14:26.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,親は気づかないうちに 誰かを\N特に可愛がってしまうのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.25,0:14:30.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういうことが生じると\N子どもたちは当惑するかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.69,0:14:33.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんな状況を考えてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.02,0:14:35.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある夫婦に二人の息子たちがいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.96,0:14:37.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,一人は開拓者です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.83,0:14:41.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は 親を悲しませるような \Nことをしません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.43,0:14:44.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう一人は 真理を  受け入れませんでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.27,0:14:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビジネスで成功を収めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.44,0:14:52.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は 経済的に両親を\N惜しみなく援助し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.44,0:14:55.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,親もそれを非常に\N感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.21,0:14:59.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,親が その息子のビジネス上の成功を\N自慢して話すのを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.75,0:15:03.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓者の息子は\Nたびたび耳にします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.12,0:15:04.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓者の息子はー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.62,0:15:07.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,物質面で親を助けることができません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.62,0:15:10.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで ちょっと不公平に感じます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.49,0:15:12.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,辛い状況ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.39,0:15:15.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,人生には こうしたことが\N生じえます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.23,0:15:18.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 開拓者の息子はー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:21.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが自分の奉仕を\N高く評価してくださり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:24.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,み名のために\N行なっていることのゆえに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.67,0:15:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分をとても愛しておられる\Nことを悟るべきです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:34.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブの場合 イサクが自分よりも\N兄を愛していることを知っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.52,0:15:39.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 子どもを設けたら\N公平に扱おうと心に誓ったことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.99,0:15:43.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも ヤコブは \Nそうはしなかったようですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨセフがお気に入りだったことに\Nみんなが気づいていたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.43,0:15:54.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて この家族の全体像をつかむのに\N必要なのはどんなことでしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.20,0:15:57.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾つかの異なる章を読みました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.14,0:16:03.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記 25, 26, 28, 29\Nそして32章です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.51,0:16:06.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある出来事の全体像を把握するには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.35,0:16:09.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでいるその章だけでは\N不十分なことがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.75,0:16:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の他の章から 詳細な情報を\N得なければならないこともあるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.46,0:16:19.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,物事の全体像をつかむことが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.26,0:16:21.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,理解を増し加えることを示す例をー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.40,0:16:24.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう一つ 手短に考慮しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.40,0:16:27.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,ナアマンに生じた出来事です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.74,0:16:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんも よくご存じでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.31,0:16:33.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,列王第二 5章1節が示すように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.51,0:16:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ナアマンは シリアの王\Nベンハダド二世の軍の長でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.11,0:16:42.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし らい病にかかっていました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.38,0:16:45.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて ベンハダドはイスラエルにー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.25,0:16:47.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エリシャという預言者がいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.22,0:16:50.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼のらい病を癒せることを知ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.26,0:16:52.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで その預言者のもとに行ってー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.70,0:16:55.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,癒しを受けるようにナアマンに告げます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.93,0:16:59.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことはイスラエルの王にも\N書面で知らされ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.40,0:17:03.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ナアマンをエリシャに見て\Nもらえるよう依頼がなされます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.27,0:17:07.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし イスラエルとシリアが\N対立関係にあったことを考えると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.88,0:17:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この依頼は奇妙に\N聞こえるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.18,0:17:14.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,戦い合うことさえあった間柄なのに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.15,0:17:15.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここでシリアの王はー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.85,0:17:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兵を率いる軍の長を遣わして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.19,0:17:21.96,Default2,,0,0,0,, “わたしの軍の長を\N もっと元気にしたいので—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.96,0:17:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“癒してもらえるよう\N 取り計らってほしい”と頼んだのです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.80,0:17:29.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,王はエリシャのところへ\N行かせ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.77,0:17:33.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,エリシャは親切に\Nナアマンを癒したのでー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.10,0:17:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼はエホバの崇拝者になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.04,0:17:41.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではここで\N想像力を働かせてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.51,0:17:43.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,シリアに帰ってきたナアマンを見て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.85,0:17:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベンハダドはどれほどエリシャに\N感謝したことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.02,0:17:53.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで めでたしめでたしということに\Nなりましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.86,0:17:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その先を読まないと \Nそう思うかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.03,0:18:01.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際には それで終わった訳では\Nありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.83,0:18:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,続く6章を読むと ベンハダドが\Nイスラエルに宣戦布告しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.17,0:18:11.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ナアマンが まだ軍の長であったならー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.41,0:18:14.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は難しい立場に立たされたでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.24,0:18:17.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを崇拝する仲間と戦うためにー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.41,0:18:20.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,シリアの軍を率いるのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.22,0:18:22.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,もっと悪いことがおきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.62,0:18:25.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベンハダドは シリア人の戦略をー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.95,0:18:29.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルの王に告げているのが\Nエリシャだと知ると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.73,0:18:32.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼を捕らえるため大軍を遣わしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.93,0:18:37.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の軍の長を癒した\Nまさにその人をです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.20,0:18:40.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんという感謝の表われでしょう \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.44,0:18:43.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いのは\N軍を率いる長として—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:46.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,ナアマンの名前が\N挙げられていないことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.78,0:18:49.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうにかして\N身を引いたのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:50.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしに聞かないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.75,0:18:54.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,復活してきたら本人に\N聞いてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.72,0:18:56.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,何を学べますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.95,0:19:00.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,世が示す感謝は\Nすぐに消えゆくものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.72,0:19:04.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,新聞やテレビで エホバの証人に関するー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.43,0:19:07.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,好意的なコメントが報じられると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.10,0:19:10.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある人は興奮するかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.23,0:19:12.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは何とおっしゃっていますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.43,0:19:14.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記 3章15節には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.84,0:19:19.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは お前と女との間に\N 敵意を置く”とあります \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.81,0:19:22.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから エホバの組織と\Nサタンの組織は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.41,0:19:25.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,絶えず対立しているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.68,0:19:30.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書通読は 退屈なものではなく\N喜びをもたらします \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.35,0:19:35.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでいることの全体像をつかむなら\N一層喜びが増すでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.16,0:19:38.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,この聖なる書物への感謝を\N深めてゆかれる皆さんを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.93,0:19:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが豊かに\N祝福してくださるよう願っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.93,0:19:46.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,では ロッキーに替わりましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.10,0:19:50.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際的な適用について\N扱ってくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.04,0:19:51.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとうございます \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.74,0:19:54.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,デービッドが指摘したとおり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.04,0:19:59.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びは 聖書通読をどのように行うかに\N深く関係しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.08,0:20:02.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のドラマでは \N一人の開拓者の姉妹が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.68,0:20:04.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,なすべきことを行っているのにー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.92,0:20:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,やる気が薄らいでいくことに気づきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.22,0:20:11.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓者でも そうでなくても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.26,0:20:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的食物を正しく消化することの\N重要性にご注目ください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.18,0:20:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ルームメイトのカミールです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.35,0:20:36.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして あの...\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これがわたしです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.79,0:20:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最近 なぜか気分がさえないんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.73,0:20:48.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,数年前に開拓奉仕を始めて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.46,0:20:52.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初はすごく奉仕に熱心だったのに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.53,0:20:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,だんだん 初めの熱意が\Nなくなってしまった...\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.67,0:21:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして すべてに\N喜びが無くなってしまったわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.76,0:21:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,正直 何が間違っているか\N分からなかった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.16,0:21:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何も悪いことをしている\Nわけじゃないし...\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.57,0:21:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“きっと疲れているだけ” と思ってた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.51,0:21:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも全然良くならない\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.48,0:21:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしに何が起きたか考えてみたわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.15,0:21:42.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに対する愛も—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.15,0:21:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆への愛も感じている\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.02,0:21:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも奉仕の意欲がわかないんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何かが足りないと感じてた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.37,0:22:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,熱意が弱まると\N集会の出席もおろそかになっていったわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.28,0:22:19.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがたいことに\N会衆の愛ある長老が気づいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.82,0:22:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに援助に来て下さった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.16,0:22:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしがどうしているか\N兄弟たちは見に来られたの\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.14,0:22:39.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしの話によく耳を傾けてから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.34,0:22:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的な習慣を尋ねて下さった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.88,0:22:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は毎日読んでいたけど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,読書はあまり好きな方ではないと\N認めたわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.02,0:22:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,するとイエスの母マリアの例を\N思い起こさせて下さったの\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.36,0:22:59.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めは関連が分からなかったけど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.06,0:23:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読んでいくうちに\N明らかになっていったわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.54,0:23:15.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリアは信仰の女性として\N知られているけど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.94,0:23:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その信仰を強めたものは\N何だったのかしら？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.72,0:23:31.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリアは霊的に意義深い言葉に\N注意を払い—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.29,0:23:34.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,聞いた事柄をじっくりと黙想し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.20,0:23:37.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,“心の中であれこれと\N 結論を下しつつ—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.50,0:23:41.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,“こうして語られる事柄すべてを\N 記憶にとどめていった”と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.80,0:23:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は述べている\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.41,0:23:52.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,マリアは霊的な事柄を\N黙想することによって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.08,0:23:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに対する信仰と熱意を強めていた\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.89,0:24:02.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かったわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.49,0:24:06.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは読んだことを黙想する時間を\N取っていなかったから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.60,0:24:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心の中の動機になっていなかったのね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.77,0:24:12.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに何かを変えなければ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.50,0:24:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的に燃え尽きてしまう\Nところだったわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.34,0:24:21.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,まずは忙しい予定を調整して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.08,0:24:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,一日を聖書通読で始めることにしたわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.62,0:24:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして静かな場所で\N読んだ事柄を黙想するの\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.82,0:24:34.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,意義深い黙想によって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.62,0:24:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにお仕えしたいという\N熱意はよみがえり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.16,0:24:40.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈りのこもった黙想は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.26,0:24:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしの焦点を元通りに\N合わせてくれたわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.04,0:24:50.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,調整してから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.37,0:24:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの奉仕の喜びを\N徐々に取り戻したわ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.69,0:25:05.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書が述べる通り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.55,0:25:10.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的な事柄を読み\N黙想する時間を取り分けるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.89,0:25:15.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは 水のほとりに\N植えられた木のようになり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.40,0:25:18.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,その葉は枯れることがなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.53,0:25:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,行なうことはすべて成功する！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.14,0:25:33.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹が聖書を毎日読んでいたことに\Nお気づきでしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.32,0:25:38.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしそれだけで必要な霊的栄養素を\Nとれるわけではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.35,0:25:43.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書通読を 無意識に行なう習慣に\Nしないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.12,0:25:46.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,無意識に行なうとは \Nどういうことでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.26,0:25:49.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば わたしたちは\N特に考えなくても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.93,0:25:54.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,息をしたり歩いたり\N自転車に乗ったりすることができます \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.54,0:25:57.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,いわば 無意識に行っているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.44,0:26:00.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じことが読むことにも\N生じえます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.91,0:26:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では どうすれば黙想を\N効果的に行なえますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.05,0:26:09.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある部分を読み終わったなら\Nいったん読むのをやめ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.12,0:26:13.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んだ事を正しく理解しているかどうか\N思い巡らしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.86,0:26:15.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう自問します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.92,0:26:19.19,Default2,,0,0,0,, “ここから エホバについて\N 何を学べるだろうか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.19,0:26:22.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自分の生活にどのように\N 適用できるだろうか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.46,0:26:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“野外宣教でどのように\N 活用できるだろうか？” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.00,0:26:29.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んだことを \N適用するようにしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.90,0:26:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 気を散らすものの少ない環境で\N読むことも集中する助けになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.28,0:26:41.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 注意を集中できる時間が短く—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.78,0:26:44.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに思いがさまよい始めるならー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.32,0:26:46.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすればよいでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.35,0:26:48.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,短い時間から初めてー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.29,0:26:50.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,徐々に長くするという方法が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.13,0:26:52.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けになるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.46,0:26:57.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,学んでいることに留まるよう努め\N急いで通り過ぎないようにします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.67,0:27:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 霊的な食物から \N爽やかさを得るでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.57,0:27:08.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,黙想のための優れた道具は\N出版物に乗せられる挿絵や写真です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.71,0:27:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,例として ダニエル5章の記述を\N取り上げましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.32,0:27:16.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.45,0:27:20.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,“まさしくその夜 \N カルデア人の王ベルシャザルは殺され—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.76,0:27:24.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,“メディア人ダリウスが\N その王国を受けた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.33,0:27:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ダリウスはおよそ六十二歳であった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.00,0:27:32.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,この出来事に関する預言を含め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.40,0:27:37.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の様々な記述を用いて\N詳細を理解することにより—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.14,0:27:39.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界本部のアート部門は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.17,0:27:43.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,鮮やかな絵で\Nその夜の様子を描き出しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.65,0:27:48.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは メディア-ペルシャの兵士たちが\Nユーフラテス川の川底を進み—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.95,0:27:53.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,開かれていた門を通って\Nバビロンの都市に入る様子です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.59,0:27:58.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,出版物にある挿絵を見ることは\N黙想の助けになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.63,0:28:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし なぜそう言えるのでしょうか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.10,0:28:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では アート部門の舞台裏を見て\Nその答えを見いだしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.74,0:28:17.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,視覚教材は大抵\N話す言葉よりも鮮明で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.91,0:28:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまでも残る印象を与えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.25,0:28:28.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,アート部門は40年近くにわたって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.42,0:28:30.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,執筆委員会の指示のもとー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.29,0:28:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書文書をデザインし準備してきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.66,0:28:42.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,この部門が設けられたのは\N1976年より 少し前のことですがー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.60,0:28:47.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,「創造の写真劇」の頃には \N すでに少人数のアーティストたちが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.34,0:28:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,挿絵や活版印刷に携わっていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.21,0:28:57.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書文書を出版する業は\N大きな変化を経てきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.65,0:29:01.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では EPUB形式や\NインタラクティブなPDFファイル\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.82,0:29:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウェブデザインや\NHTML形式などがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.09,0:29:09.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらすべてには\N新しい技術が求められ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.10,0:29:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテル内の多くの部門との\N密な協力関係が必要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.97,0:29:19.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,アート部門は\Nいくつかのチームで構成されており—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.21,0:29:23.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,各チームには \Nデザイナーやカメラマン\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.31,0:29:25.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,挿絵画家\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.01,0:29:27.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,美術スタッフ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.22,0:29:29.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,衣装・メイク係\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.42,0:29:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 生産スタッフがいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.19,0:29:35.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,チームリーダーと\Nスケジュール管理者は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.12,0:29:40.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,執筆部門コンタクトの編集者と\N直接やり取りします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.26,0:29:42.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,テキストの草案を受け取ると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.40,0:29:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,３人の兄弟たちが その目的と\Nデザイン案について話し合います \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.07,0:29:52.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,コンセプトがまとまってくると\Nチームの全員が集められ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.94,0:29:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,プロジェクトの大まかな案に\Nそれぞれが貢献します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.41,0:30:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際の作業を始める前に\Nコンセプトをスケッチしてまとめます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.76,0:30:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,このスケッチを見て\Nチームはコンセプトを理解し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.90,0:30:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,材料を決め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.23,0:30:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,プロジェクトが\N本題からそれないようにします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.91,0:30:26.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,対象となるのは だれなのか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.74,0:30:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この出版物は\Nどのように用いられるのか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.18,0:30:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,シンプルで わかりやすいデザインを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.75,0:30:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべての言語で提供します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.19,0:30:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,簡単なことではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.39,0:30:47.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,デザインが準備できると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.23,0:30:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,編集者は 出版物の試作品を\N執筆委員会に提出します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.50,0:30:57.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,委員会は デザインを確認し\N必要な調整をします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.61,0:30:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,コンセプトが承認されるとー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.51,0:31:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,制作が始まります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.95,0:31:05.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中にいる大勢のカメラマンが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.95,0:31:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,画像を提供する奉仕を\Nパートタイムでしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.69,0:31:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,写真撮影は スタジオや\Nそのほかの場所でも行なわれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.03,0:31:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,このような写真により\N出版物に国際的な彩りが添えられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.90,0:31:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,正確さは肝要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.87,0:31:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,調査する人は\N歴史的資料やアイデアを提供します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.84,0:31:37.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,髪型や—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.71,0:31:39.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,メイク また 衣装を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.75,0:31:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,時代背景や地域に合わせて\Nデザインします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.59,0:31:48.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,小道具や大道具 照明によって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.22,0:31:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらしい背景が出来上がります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.69,0:31:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それぞれの要素が組み合わさると\Nストーリーができあがり— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.73,0:32:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,見る人の注意を引きつけます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.74,0:32:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,3Dで背景を組むこともあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.37,0:32:07.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,美術的資料としたり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.18,0:32:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最終的な挿絵として用います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.05,0:32:23.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,デジタル的か \N本来の原料で描くかに関わらず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.73,0:32:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,画家は最終的な使用に沿うかたちで\N挿絵を描きます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.00,0:32:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,インフォグラフィックスと呼ばれる\N図と挿絵を合わせたものもあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.01,0:32:46.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,執筆委員会から最終承認が下りると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.11,0:32:49.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,ファイルは プリンタリーや\Nウェブサイトに送られるか\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.28,0:32:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,デジタル版作成のために\N使われます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.26,0:32:59.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書に基づく出版物を読む人の\N心に達するためには—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.63,0:33:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際に手を使い 心を込めなければ \Nこの仕事は行なえません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.00,0:33:06.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,アート部門にいる わたしたちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.57,0:33:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最も緊急な業をサポートできることを\N特権だと感じています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.04,0:33:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 良いたよりを宣べ伝える業です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.22,0:33:31.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,質問の答えが見いだせましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.49,0:33:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ 出版物の挿絵を見ることは\N助けになるのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.26,0:33:38.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ナレーターが語っていた通り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.40,0:33:42.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,“視覚教材は大抵\N 話す言葉よりも鮮明で—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.04,0:33:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“いつまでも残る\N 印象を与え”るからです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.01,0:33:51.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,加えて 挿絵により\Nその出来事が生き生きとよみがえります \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.38,0:33:54.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,生じた出来事を目の前に\N思い描くことで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.55,0:33:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の真理や エホバ神への\N感謝を深めることができるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.86,0:34:05.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,挿絵や写真が\N大きな助けになるとはいえ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.29,0:34:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的な食物の源は\N書き記された神の言葉そのものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.47,0:34:14.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 仮にー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.90,0:34:16.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらすべてを用いることがー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.80,0:34:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,できない状況におかれるとしたら\Nどうでしょうか\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.14,0:34:21.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を持つことができずー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.98,0:34:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,挿絵の載った出版物も\Nビデオも 録音物もないとしたらです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.08,0:34:29.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしますか\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.22,0:34:31.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前に読んだことを\N思い起こすことによりー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.79,0:34:34.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊性を保つことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.42,0:34:36.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロシアの一人の兄弟はー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.19,0:34:38.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのような状況に直面しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.73,0:34:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が助けになったかに注目しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.60,0:34:52.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは1963年のことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.57,0:34:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは36歳でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.94,0:35:00.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,KGBはわたしの家の中を捜索し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.18,0:35:05.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾らかの聖書文書と伝道者の\N奉仕報告を見つけました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.12,0:35:10.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは活動を組織したかどで\N5年の刑を言い渡されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.12,0:35:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,投獄はこれで3度目でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.26,0:35:20.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミール兄弟を励ますため\N数人の兄弟姉妹が法廷に行きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.40,0:35:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちを見ると兄弟は手を握り締め\N“大丈夫です”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.08,0:35:32.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,KGBの役人が言うには\Nわたしが投獄されないのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.38,0:35:36.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしには6人の子どもがいるが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.52,0:35:38.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミールは独身だからでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.95,0:35:40.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族がいなかったので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.72,0:35:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが投獄されて\Nよかったと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.36,0:35:52.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,収容所では聖書も聖書文書も\N全くありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.93,0:35:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それまでに学んだ知識で\Nやっていくしかありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.91,0:36:01.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟のために祈り あいさつや\N励みとなるメッセージを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.78,0:36:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟の親族を通して送りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.45,0:36:07.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,厳しい検閲のため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.15,0:36:12.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,手紙には互いに励まし合うための\N霊的なことは一切書けませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.25,0:36:16.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうしたとしても\N手紙は没収されたでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.59,0:36:18.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもわたしはミハイル兄弟に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.96,0:36:22.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か励みになるものを\N贈りたいと願っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.93,0:36:28.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,収容所ではほかの収容者と\N一緒に花を育てていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.10,0:36:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで手紙の代わりに\N花のブーケを贈ることにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.11,0:36:38.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミールの姉妹のオルガが\N家にやって来て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:40.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミールからの\Nきれいな花のブーケをー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.62,0:36:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,届けてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.39,0:36:53.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,有刺鉄線の向こうの収容所の中から\N生の花束を受け取るとは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.93,0:36:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,全く信じがたいことでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.80,0:37:01.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼の親切な行ないに\N心を打たれたわたしはー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.17,0:37:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,数節の詩を作り\Nそれに“ブーケ”という題をつけました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.98,0:37:12.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,親族が収容所のわたしを\N訪ねてくれたとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.61,0:37:15.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,その詩を届けてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.32,0:37:18.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,その詩は秘密の場所に\N隠しておきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.59,0:37:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは神に関するものでしたから\N没収され 処罰されかねませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.49,0:37:27.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミールは釈放後—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.50,0:37:30.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしの詩によって\N本当に強められたことやー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.63,0:37:33.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,秘密の隠し場所から\Nそれを取り出しては—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.33,0:37:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾度も幾度も読み返したことを\N話してくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.81,0:37:43.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,友の祈りやエホバからの支えが\Nなかったなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.31,0:37:48.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしがエホバに仕えることは\Nもっと難しいものになっていたはずです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.68,0:37:53.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,受け取った詩は自分が友から\Nまた最も重要なことにエホバから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.75,0:37:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,切り離されてはいないことを\N感じさせてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.86,0:38:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あれからずいぶん経ちましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.00,0:38:05.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,難しい時期を切り抜けて\Nしっかりと立ち続け—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.83,0:38:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今もエホバに仕えています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.64,0:38:15.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,最近はウラジミールと\N電話で連絡をとるようにしていますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.38,0:38:18.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,この7年間 互いに会っていません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.75,0:38:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミールに\Nまた会いたい気持ちでいっぱいです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.95,0:38:27.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが訪問することにしたことを\N彼は知りません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.59,0:38:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,びっくりして喜んでくれると思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.99,0:39:07.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,丹精込めて咲かせた花\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.43,0:39:10.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,労役で荒れた手によって咲かせた花\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.53,0:39:12.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,友が贈ってくれたブーケ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.97,0:39:15.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,三度 会うことはかなわなかった\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.87,0:39:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは挨拶を送る手立てを見出した\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.27,0:39:22.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは喜びに満たされて言おう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.24,0:39:24.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしの兄弟へー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.05,0:39:26.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,“心を込めて あいさつを送ろう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.85,0:39:29.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,“離れていてもあなたは強めてくれた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.65,0:39:34.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,“幾多の試練のただ中で\N 力を尽くし 強めてくれた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.39,0:39:38.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,“狭い通路にいる友よ \N あいさつを送ろう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.79,0:39:43.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,“多くの苦難のただ中で\N わたしたちはいつも一緒だった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.40,0:39:47.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,“霊的な宝のために共に力を尽くした”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.37,0:39:50.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,“二人の固いきずなは祝福そのもの”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.94,0:39:53.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わが友は 無残にも引き放されー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.41,0:39:56.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,“我々の忠誠は打ち砕かれようとした”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.41,0:40:00.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかし 神は立ち上がり\N 助けてくださる”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.61,0:40:05.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,“我々は悪を征服し\N 王国の希望のために戦った”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.49,0:40:09.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,“感謝に満たされ　\N これからも感謝をささげよう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.52,0:40:12.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,“将来の霊的な希望のゆえに—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.09,0:40:17.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自ら忠節の道に留まる者に\N 約束された命の冠のゆえに”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.80,0:40:22.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,“辛抱強い友よ　\N あなたはどれほど耐え忍んだか”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.70,0:40:25.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバの憐れみは決して絶えない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.64,0:40:31.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,”地上のパラダイスで手を取り合い\N エホバの目を楽しませる花を咲かせよう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.78,0:40:36.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,“キリスト・イエスはわたしたちを癒し\N 罪は跡形もなくなるであろう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.88,0:40:39.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,“耐え抜いた試練を忘れ去り—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.15,0:40:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“とこしえにわたって\N エホバの偉大なみ名を賛美しよう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.86,0:40:51.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の友はエホバからの祝福です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.97,0:40:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして誰が真の友かは\N災いの時に明らかになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.61,0:41:02.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理の道を歩んできた人生において—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.58,0:41:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはよく詩編 119編63節の\N次の言葉を考えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.25,0:41:13.49,Default2,,0,0,0,, “わたしはあなたを真に恐れる\N すべての者たちの—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.49,0:41:18.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,“また あなたの命令を守る者たちの\N 仲間なのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.06,0:41:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,共に王国の業を行なうとき\Nわたしたちの友情は強くなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.43,0:41:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠に続くのは\Nそのような友情だけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.24,0:41:38.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい友情ですね! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.75,0:41:43.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの兄弟関係は\Nまさにエホバからの祝福です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.18,0:41:47.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミハイル・サビツキー兄弟は\N長年にわたりシベリアやカフカス北部— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.99,0:41:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらにはグルジアやアルメニアで\N巡回奉仕に携わり —\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.23,0:41:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国の業の進展を助けてきました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.40,0:41:59.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,1992年 兄弟は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.23,0:42:02.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロシアでの業の法的認可に関する書面にー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.37,0:42:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,署名する特権にあずかりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.41,0:42:10.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,残念なことに\Nこのビデオの制作から程なくして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.51,0:42:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミール・バルクホリック兄弟は\N死の眠りにつきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.05,0:42:22.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,88歳で 59年以上に渡って\Nエホバに忠実に仕えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.92,0:42:26.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,亡くなる段階で\N26年間開拓者としてー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.83,0:42:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,43年間会衆の長老として\N奉仕しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.87,0:42:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,このインタビューから\N明らかなように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.00,0:42:36.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,投獄されている12年間—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.14,0:42:40.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟はその信仰ゆえに\N霊的な強さを保てました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.98,0:42:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの良い手本です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.91,0:42:49.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟が投獄されていた様子について\Nお気づきになりましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.95,0:42:56.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は “収容所では 聖書も\N聖書文書も全くありませんでした”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.49,0:43:00.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それまでに学んだ知識で\N やっていくしかありませんでした”とー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.06,0:43:01.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,語っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.66,0:43:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じことは\Nわたしたちにも生じえます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.03,0:43:08.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,迫害のために備えをしておく\N必要があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.50,0:43:11.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのためにも\N時が許されている限り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.14,0:43:15.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の研究を\Nおろそかにすべきではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.61,0:43:18.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,では デービッドと\N代わります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.71,0:43:20.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとうございました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.51,0:43:24.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウラジミール兄弟のことを\N残念に思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.79,0:43:28.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし エホバ神がそのみ名のために\N兄弟が示した愛を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.72,0:43:31.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,決してお忘れにならないのは確かです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.66,0:43:34.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,心を動かされるインタビューでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.70,0:43:41.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて 6月に新しい王国の歌が何曲か\N電子的に配信されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.30,0:43:45.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし151番だけが抜けていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.04,0:43:46.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,お気づきでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.47,0:43:51.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹の目が節穴ではないことは\Nわかっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.31,0:43:54.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではここで151番をご紹介しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.88,0:43:59.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は \N“神の子たちが表わし示される”です \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.19,0:44:02.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,残りの者たちが 天に行くときが\N近づいていることを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.22,0:44:04.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,思い起こさせる歌です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.26,0:44:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 聞きましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.19,0:46:20.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,美しい歌でしたね！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.96,0:46:22.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.16,0:46:24.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に美しい歌です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.06,0:46:27.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ものみの塔のコーラス隊には\N本当に感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.77,0:46:30.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,プロの訓練を受けているのは\N2-3人で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.44,0:46:34.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の皆さんは ひたすら努力して\Nこれほどまでになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.14,0:46:36.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,その点に注目できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.21,0:46:39.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちも\N歌を練習し 練習し 練習し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.68,0:46:43.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国会館で\N大きな声で歌いましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.48,0:46:48.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,終わりが近づいているので\N本当に時宜にかなった歌だといえます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.89,0:46:54.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,この体制の終わりが近づくにつれ\N野外宣教でなすべきことは多くあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.70,0:46:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 仕事のために\N家ではほとんど会えない人々もいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.00,0:47:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨーロッパの兄弟姉妹はそうした人々に\N達する方法を見つけました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.38,0:47:20.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎年 世界中から来た\N何千人ものトラック運転手が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.59,0:47:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨーロッパ大陸を縦横に走っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.73,0:47:27.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族の生計を立てるため\N懸命に働き—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.96,0:47:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,数週間家を離れることも\N珍しくありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.93,0:47:36.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスと弟子たちは人が\Nどこにいようと近づきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.74,0:47:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちも同じ願いを持っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.07,0:47:44.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこでも運転手のいる場所へ行き—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.18,0:47:46.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうしなければ会えない人も含め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.38,0:47:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべての人が証言を受けるよう\N努力が払われています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.52,0:47:54.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,トラックの多い\Nロッテルダムに住んでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.35,0:47:57.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,通常の区域は3か月に1度\N網羅していますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.62,0:48:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,トラック運転手にはめったに会えません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.10,0:48:07.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎年30万台のトラックが\Nフランスを横断しており—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.23,0:48:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大きな可能性のある分野を\N開拓する必要がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.64,0:48:18.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,たくさんの運転手が駐車場で\N休憩し 泊まっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.75,0:48:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教に絶好の場所です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.85,0:48:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,駐車している間 休憩や洗車をします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.03,0:48:37.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここには洗濯場がないので\N衣類を洗っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.43,0:48:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,料理もします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.87,0:48:46.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある日 フランスに行く途中—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.34,0:48:50.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,オーストリアで車を停めて\N運転を交代しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.61,0:48:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,同僚はトイレに行き\Nわたしは一人でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.55,0:49:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その時 証人がやって来て\N雑誌を勧めてきたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.76,0:49:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,証言が組織的に行なわれるよう\N多くの努力が払われています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.20,0:49:11.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべての駐車場を地図にして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.40,0:49:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓者が一日に一度はこの区域で\N証言できるよう計画を立てています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.64,0:49:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕者は多くの国籍や\N言語の人に出会います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.21,0:49:28.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,言語の壁は最も大きな障害です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.42,0:49:30.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,午前だけでルーマニア語\Nロシア語—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.92,0:49:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ポーランド語など\N10言語に出くわします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.22,0:49:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,雑誌を見ると\Nドイツ語の「ものみの塔」でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.36,0:49:43.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドイツ語を話せないと言うと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.43,0:49:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その兄弟は車のナンバープレートを見て\Nルーマニア語であることに気付きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.44,0:49:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ルーマニア語の雑誌です どうぞ”と\Nもう一度雑誌を勧めてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.18,0:49:59.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても嬉しかったです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.35,0:50:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜んで雑誌を受け取りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.72,0:50:08.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 1世紀のクリスチャンのように\N異言は話せませんが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.39,0:50:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,jw.orgのおかげで\Nどんな言語でも証言できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.00,0:50:20.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,出版物を配布する以上のことが必要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.73,0:50:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の教え手になるために\Nビデオを活用しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.71,0:50:34.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある運転手はダッシュボードの上に\N聖書を広げたまま—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.25,0:50:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「聖書を学ぶべきなのはなぜですか」の\N ビデオを見て声をあげて泣きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.72,0:50:45.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,トラック運転手はほとんどの時間を\N道路の上で過ごすため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.63,0:50:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,関心を示した人に再び会うことは\N容易ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.10,0:50:57.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,再訪問し研究を始めることは\N非常に難しいと感じます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.10,0:50:59.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまた会えるかわかりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.11,0:51:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それですぐにメールアドレスを\N聞くようにしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.41,0:51:09.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,結果は驚くべきものでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.22,0:51:15.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば昨奉仕年度中\N約10万冊の雑誌が配布され—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.06,0:51:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,100件の研究が始まり\N4千回ビデオを見せることができました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.80,0:51:27.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえメールアドレスを\N聞けなかったとしても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.23,0:51:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,少しの証言が大きな影響を\N与えうることを経験は示しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.44,0:51:37.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがてルーマニアに戻りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.24,0:51:40.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書研究を始め 霊的に成長し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.25,0:51:44.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚して 今はバプテスマを\N受けていない伝道者です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.18,0:51:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初にわたしに接した兄弟は\N知らないでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.36,0:51:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘブライ 6章11節は 宣教で\N「勤勉さを示す」よう皆に勧めています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.40,0:52:00.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,この宣教に時間を\N費やせば費やすほど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.23,0:52:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,運転手の良い反応から\N達成感を得られます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.47,0:52:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,トラックの駐車場で良いたよりを\N伝えるのは素晴らしいことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.28,0:52:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,運転手は皆 神の愛を感じ\N神の気遣いを知る必要があるからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.32,0:52:24.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしのように 彼らも\N生き方を変えることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.89,0:52:27.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが将来の楽園を約束しておられ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.53,0:52:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それが自分と家族にどんな影響を\N及ぼすかを理解する必要があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.20,0:52:40.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい結果をともなう\N証言方法ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.97,0:52:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,携わる皆さんが宣教で\Nビデオを活用する姿を見るのも喜びです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.65,0:52:49.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオは優れた道具ですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.98,0:52:51.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは引き続きー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.65,0:52:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書から論じる技術を\N磨いていく必要があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.99,0:53:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,トラック駐車場で証言する兄弟たちは\Nまさにそうしてきました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.00,0:53:04.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして良い結果が生まれています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.73,0:53:08.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜ばしいことに インタビューを受けた\Nイオン・ボルボティナは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.90,0:53:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最近バプテスマを受けて\Nエホバの証人になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.94,0:53:16.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教における わたしたちの努力を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.21,0:53:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが祝福してくださるのは\N喜ばしいことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.01,0:53:23.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,マルガリータ･ケニガー姉妹は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.18,0:53:26.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,生涯にわたって王国の業の増加を\N見てきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.92,0:53:30.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,1966年から\N宣教者として奉仕していて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.69,0:53:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,過去9年間は\Nハンガリーで奉仕してきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.11,0:53:47.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブタペストは美しい都市です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.61,0:53:51.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,様々な国に囲まれていて\Nここは人種のるつぼです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.98,0:53:53.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても国際的です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.98,0:53:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハンガリーの都市ですが\Nあらゆる場所の人が通っていきます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.29,0:54:06.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは中国語の畑で\N奉仕する宣教者でー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.09,0:54:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここで9年になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.46,0:54:15.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教者になって47年になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.14,0:54:18.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初の割り当ては\Nマダガスカルでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.47,0:54:20.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い研究を持っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.67,0:54:22.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても良い人たちだったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.98,0:54:25.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,マダガスカルに4年半いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.55,0:54:29.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 禁令になったため\N出て行く必要があり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.75,0:54:31.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,追い出されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.65,0:54:33.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾らか荷物を持っていけましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.85,0:54:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,もともと物はあまりありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.76,0:54:40.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 ケニアに遣わされます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.69,0:54:44.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,3年後 またもや禁令になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.80,0:54:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでベニンに来ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.10,0:54:49.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,知り合いに少し証言しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.57,0:54:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 彼らは当時 共産主義者に\Nなっていたため注意が必要でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.01,0:55:01.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある日 軍と警察がやって来ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.95,0:55:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,スローガンを叫ぶ若者もいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.25,0:55:10.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エ フズ！ダンダン！\N エ フズ！ダンダン！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.66,0:55:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自由になる！\N 自由になる！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.73,0:55:16.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても興奮していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.80,0:55:19.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルは取り囲まれ出られません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.67,0:55:22.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは悪人とされたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.97,0:55:26.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,次の日 大柄な警察官が二人来ました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.94,0:55:29.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,“来なさい トーゴに連れて行く”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.88,0:55:31.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,その通りにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.58,0:55:33.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,荷物はありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.48,0:55:36.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,トーゴにいくために出発しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.85,0:55:39.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,ずっと彼らに証言しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.09,0:55:43.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,一人が証言し\Nもう一人は祈っていたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.99,0:55:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバについてずっと話しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.83,0:55:50.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから森で止まり\Nこう言われます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.33,0:55:52.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,“車から降りろ！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.33,0:55:57.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが正しい考えを与えてくださり\N“降りません”と答えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.34,0:56:01.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈り そこに座ったまま\N動きませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.34,0:56:04.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らが話し合っている間\N“もし彼らが来ても—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.94,0:56:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“降りなくて済むようできることは\N 何でもしよう”と考えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.15,0:56:12.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らが戻って来て \N“よし では行こう”と言い—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.49,0:56:15.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのまま出発しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.19,0:56:17.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,危なかったです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.16,0:56:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはわたしの宣教者奉仕で\N一番危険な時でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.50,0:56:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人の姉妹だけでしたからね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.03,0:56:31.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちはトーゴに\N連れて行かれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.77,0:56:36.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから4週間ほど待ち\N新しい割り当てを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.31,0:56:38.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブルキナファソです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.68,0:56:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,23年間その国にいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.65,0:56:47.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,市場に行って買い物をしていると\N皆わたしのこと知っていて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.19,0:56:51.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,“マダム・モアガ マダム・モアガ”と\N 呼んできます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.62,0:56:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,モアガとは原住民 モシ人のことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.96,0:57:00.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,モシは部族の名前で\Nモシ族の人をモアガと言います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.83,0:57:03.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでわたしはマダム・モアガです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.97,0:57:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らの言語を上手に話したからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.54,0:57:10.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々から学びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.74,0:57:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで安く買い物ができました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.55,0:57:20.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,反応はとても良く\Nいつもバプテスマを受ける人がいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.79,0:57:25.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,一年で10人 \N少なくとも8人はいたと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.06,0:57:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても小さな始まりでしたが\N成長していきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.87,0:57:35.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年奉仕したあと\Nマラリアにかかったため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.54,0:57:37.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドイツに遣わされました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.84,0:57:43.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 ここハンガリーに遣わされ\N来て9年になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.34,0:57:47.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブダペストには幾千人もの\N中国人が住んでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.21,0:57:52.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,中国人の店やレストラン\N小さな飲食店で証言しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.12,0:57:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても友好的で 今では大勢が\Nわたしのことを知っているんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.56,0:58:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは中国語会衆が大好きです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.77,0:58:13.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らは他の中国人やエホバの証人に\N会うためにも来ていて帰りたがりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.87,0:58:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い霊があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.61,0:58:22.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはエホバにとても感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.35,0:58:23.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょうど良い時にー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.65,0:58:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しい生き方に飛び込むよう\N助けてくださったからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.92,0:58:33.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,全時間奉仕は旅行—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.49,0:58:36.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが導いてくださる\N旅行のようです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.66,0:58:39.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから心配はいりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.10,0:58:42.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが責任を持ってくださるからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.37,0:58:45.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの責任は忠実であることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.91,0:58:49.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が生じているか\Nエホバはご存じで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.44,0:58:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがお許しになることは\N大丈夫なんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.28,0:58:58.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い人には皆 同じようにすることを\N願っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.79,0:59:02.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても満足いく生き方を\N逃して欲しくないのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.99,0:59:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと共に働くことに\N比べられるものは何もありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.96,0:59:14.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギレアデを卒業してから\N50年の間に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.30,0:59:20.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ケニガー姉妹は 七つの言語を学び\N五つの国で奉仕ししてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.27,0:59:23.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,最近 姉妹は \N新たな割り当てを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.88,0:59:27.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドイツ ミュンヘンの\N中国語の区域です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.48,0:59:32.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹は 神の言葉を毎日読み\N黙想することによって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.22,0:59:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教者としての割り当てを\N喜びのうちに続ける力を得てきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.56,0:59:42.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは 若い皆さんにとっても重要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.73,0:59:45.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的な食物を十分取り入れー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.37,0:59:48.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書通読の質を高めるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.20,0:59:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しい決定を下すことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.24,0:59:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえば どんな人を\N友とすべきですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.01,1:00:01.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,“僕のいる場所”と題する\N ミュージックビデオに注目しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.65,1:00:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最善の友を選ぶ助けになるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.73,1:00:20.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,さぁ どこに 根を張り\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.77,1:00:25.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう どこで 咲かせる？\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.71,1:00:30.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,答えは 分かってる\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.74,1:00:35.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕がいるべき場所\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.52,1:00:40.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,目を見て 分かり合う\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.39,1:00:45.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,胸の奥 引き出す\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.16,1:00:50.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当の 仲間は\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.30,1:00:54.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここにしかいない\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.90,1:00:59.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,やわらかく\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.74,1:01:04.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,咲きはじめる\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.84,1:01:09.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバから\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.82,1:01:14.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛そそがれ\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.49,1:01:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕のいる場所\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.34,1:01:34.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう 今は 見えている\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.04,1:01:38.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこにいたいのか\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.88,1:01:43.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの声 聞いて\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.95,1:01:48.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,心は燃えてく\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.82,1:01:51.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,さぁ 行こう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.19,1:01:53.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れずに\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.76,1:01:58.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕らは 独りじゃない\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.56,1:02:03.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当の友情は\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.50,1:02:08.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛の贈り物\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.27,1:02:13.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,やわらかく\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.11,1:02:18.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,照らされる\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.02,1:02:23.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバから\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.02,1:02:27.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,光 受け\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.86,1:02:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,僕のいる場所\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.68,1:02:46.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい若者ですね！\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.58,1:02:48.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は正しい決定を下し—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.88,1:02:52.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの組織に\N自分のいる場所を見いだしました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.65,1:02:55.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな習慣を保っていましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.22,1:03:00.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を定期的に読み \N旅行にも携えていきました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.03,1:03:06.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 通読の途中にも 宣教の間も\N読んだことを黙想していました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.67,1:03:12.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに エホバの創造のみ業について\N思い巡らす時間を取り分けました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.51,1:03:14.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちもそうしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.61,1:03:17.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書通読の質を高めましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.51,1:03:21.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んだことを思いに描き\N全体像をつかみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.75,1:03:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の記述を思いに描く点で\N組織は素晴らしい道具を備えてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.09,1:03:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,出版物の挿絵 音声劇 \N劇形式の聖書朗読 そしてビデオなどです\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.00,1:03:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらを十分に活用し\N学んだことを黙想してください\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.17,1:03:45.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロッキー わたしもまったく同感です\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.97,1:03:49.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて 9月1日以降—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.24,1:03:52.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテル家族はブルックリンから\Nニューヨーク ウォーウィックのー\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.85,1:03:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,新たな世界本部に移転します\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.15,1:04:01.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,英国の皆さんにとっては\N“ウォーイック”かもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.05,1:04:02.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ウォーウィック”\N“ ウォーイック”—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.62,1:04:06.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,“トマト” “トメイト”\Nどちらも同じです\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.43,1:04:10.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちはこの移転を\N本当に喜んでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.56,1:04:14.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブルックリンからウォーウィックに\Nベテル家族を移動させるのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.17,1:04:18.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に大きなプロジェクトで\N時間もかかるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.67,1:04:22.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい本部を実際に見てみたいと\N思うかもしれませんが—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.38,1:04:26.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,準備が整って\N2017年4月3日 月曜日に—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.25,1:04:29.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,見学が開始されるまで\Nお待ちください\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.92,1:04:31.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう一度いいますね\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.88,1:04:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,見学ができるのは\N2017年4月3日からです\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.19,1:04:43.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,それまでの間にウォールキルや\Nパタソンを見学する機会があるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.83,1:04:48.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウォーウィックまで来て\N周囲の森に入って 木によじ登り—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.97,1:04:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界本部をちょっとでも見たいという\N誘惑に駆られるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.01,1:04:56.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはやめましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.14,1:05:00.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんをきちんとお迎えできるよう\N一生懸命 準備しています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.85,1:05:06.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,施設を見学できるようにするため\N良く整えたいと思っています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.82,1:05:12.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深い取り決めとして オンラインで\N見学を申し込めるようになります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.79,1:05:18.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆や支部と協力して 見学のための\N取り決めが設けられていくでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.93,1:05:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,慌てて駆け込まなくても大丈夫です\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.07,1:05:28.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,加えて “生命の起源に対する見方”に—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.34,1:05:33.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,二つのインタビューが加わり\N視聴可能になったことをお知らせします\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.55,1:05:35.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,4月に始まった このシリーズには—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.95,1:05:38.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,命が 偶然によってではなくー\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.35,1:05:41.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,設計の所産として\N生じるようになったという—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.69,1:05:45.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,結論に至った科学者たちが登場します\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.59,1:05:47.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,“経験とインタビュー”の\Nセクションにある—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.99,1:05:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,, “生命の起源に対する見方”の\N 見出しから視聴できます\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.43,1:06:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 結びに ボリビア北東部の\Nベニからの挨拶をお送りしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.11,1:06:07.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,この地域では 人口426人に一人の\N割合で伝道者がいます\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.08,1:06:12.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,区域は 多くの川と\Nジャングルからなっています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.22,1:06:17.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,リベラルタとグアヤラメリンには\N350名ほどの伝道者がいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.62,1:06:21.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,区域の隅々に達するため\N創意工夫をしています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.53,1:06:24.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 支部の指導の下—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.10,1:06:30.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,証人のパイロットの操縦する飛行機で\N孤立した集落を訪問しています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.44,1:06:35.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 川のほとりにある集落には\N船でしか行くことができません\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.57,1:06:40.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのため 船による証言旅行が\N時おり 計画されています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.95,1:06:44.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,旅行が 一か月以上に\N及ぶこともあります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.82,1:06:48.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに バイクでしか行けない\N区域もあります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.29,1:06:50.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらの区域を網羅するため—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.26,1:06:54.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹が四時間かけて\N移動することもあります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.66,1:06:58.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベニの兄弟姉妹が\N温かい愛を送っています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.96,1:07:02.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちも 世界中の皆さんに\N愛を送ります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.67,1:07:05.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロッキー プログラムの提供に\N協力してくださりー\N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.71,1:07:07.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとうございました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.27,1:07:09.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に助けになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.28,1:07:10.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,こちらこそ\N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.48,1:07:13.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューヨーク市 ブルックリンから\NJW Broadcasting でした!\N
